296template <bool> struct conditional_helper;
297
298template <> struct conditional_helper<true> {
299 template <typename A, typename> using type = A;
300};
301
302template <> struct conditional_helper<false> {
303 template <typename, typename B> using type = B;
304};
305
306template <bool V, typename A, typename B> using conditional = typename conditional_helper<V>::template type<A,B>;
307
308}

312namespace ctll {
313
314struct length_value_t {
315 uint32_t value;
316 uint8_t length;
317};
318
319constexpr length_value_t length_and_value_of_utf8_code_point(uint8_t first_unit) noexcept {
320 if ((first_unit & 0b1000'0000) == 0b0000'0000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit), 1};
321 else if ((first_unit & 0b1110'0000) == 0b1100'0000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0001'1111), 2};
322 else if ((first_unit & 0b1111'0000) == 0b1110'0000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0000'1111), 3};
323 else if ((first_unit & 0b1111'1000) == 0b1111'0000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0000'0111), 4};
324 else if ((first_unit & 0b1111'1100) == 0b1111'1000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0000'0011), 5};
325 else if ((first_unit & 0b1111'1100) == 0b1111'1100) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0000'0001), 6};
326 else return {0, 0};
327}
328
329constexpr char32_t value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(uint8_t unit, bool & correct) noexcept {
330 if ((unit & 0b1100'0000) == 0b1000'0000) return unit & 0b0011'1111;
331 else {
332 correct = false;
333 return 0;
334 }
335}
336
337constexpr length_value_t length_and_value_of_utf16_code_point(uint16_t first_unit) noexcept {
338 if ((first_unit & 0b1111110000000000) == 0b1101'1000'0000'0000) return {static_cast<uint32_t>(first_unit & 0b0000001111111111), 2};
339 else return {first_unit, 1};
340}
341
342struct construct_from_pointer_t { };
343
344constexpr auto construct_from_pointer = construct_from_pointer_t{};
345
346CTLL_EXPORT template <size_t N> struct fixed_string {
347 char32_t content[N] = {};
348 size_t real_size{0};
349 bool correct_flag{true};
350
351 template <typename T> constexpr fixed_string(construct_from_pointer_t, const T * input) noexcept {
352 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, char>) {
353 #ifdef CTRE_STRING_IS_UTF8
354 size_t out{0};
355 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
356 if ((i == (N-1)) && (input[i] == 0)) break;
357 length_value_t info = length_and_value_of_utf8_code_point(input[i]);
358 switch (info.length) {
359 case 6:
360 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
361 [[fallthrough]];
362 case 5:
363 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
364 [[fallthrough]];
365 case 4:
366 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
367 [[fallthrough]];
368 case 3:
369 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
370 [[fallthrough]];
371 case 2:
372 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
373 [[fallthrough]];
374 case 1:
375 content[out++] = static_cast<char32_t>(info.value);
376 real_size++;
377 break;
378 default:
379 correct_flag = false;
380 return;
381 }
382 }
383 #else
384 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
385 content[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(input[i]);
386 if ((i == (N-1)) && (input[i] == 0)) break;
387 real_size++;
388 }
389 #endif
390 #if __cpp_char8_t
391 } else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, char8_t>) {
392 size_t out{0};
393 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
394 if ((i == (N-1)) && (input[i] == 0)) break;
395 length_value_t info = length_and_value_of_utf8_code_point(input[i]);
396 switch (info.length) {
397 case 6:
398 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
399 [[fallthrough]];
400 case 5:
401 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
402 [[fallthrough]];
403 case 4:
404 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
405 [[fallthrough]];
406 case 3:
407 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
408 [[fallthrough]];
409 case 2:
410 if (++i < N) info.value = (info.value << 6) | value_of_trailing_utf8_code_point(input[i], correct_flag);
411 [[fallthrough]];
412 case 1:
413 content[out++] = static_cast<char32_t>(info.value);
414 real_size++;
415 break;
416 default:
417 correct_flag = false;
418 return;
419 }
420 }
421 #endif
422 } else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, char16_t>) {
423 size_t out{0};
424 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
425 length_value_t info = length_and_value_of_utf16_code_point(input[i]);
426 if (info.length == 2) {
427 if (++i < N) {
428 if ((input[i] & 0b1111'1100'0000'0000) == 0b1101'1100'0000'0000) {
429 content[out++] = ((info.value << 10) | (input[i] & 0b0000'0011'1111'1111)) + 0x10000;
430 } else {
431 correct_flag = false;
432 break;
433 }
434 }
435 } else {
436 if ((i == (N-1)) && (input[i] == 0)) break;
437 content[out++] = info.value;
438 }
439 }
440 real_size = out;
441 } else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<T, wchar_t> || std::is_same_v<T, char32_t>) {
442 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
443 content[i] = static_cast<char32_t>(input[i]);
444 if ((i == (N-1)) && (input[i] == 0)) break;
445 real_size++;
446 }
447 }
448 }
449
450 template <typename T> constexpr fixed_string(const std::array<T, N> & in) noexcept: fixed_string{construct_from_pointer, in.data()} { }
451 template <typename T> constexpr fixed_string(const T (&input)[N+1]) noexcept: fixed_string{construct_from_pointer, input} { }
452
453 constexpr fixed_string(const fixed_string & other) noexcept {
454 for (size_t i{0}; i < N; ++i) {
455 content[i] = other.content[i];
456 }
457 real_size = other.real_size;
458 correct_flag = other.correct_flag;
459 }
460 constexpr bool correct() const noexcept {
461 return correct_flag;
462 }
463 constexpr size_t size() const noexcept {
464 return real_size;
465 }
466 constexpr const char32_t * begin() const noexcept {
467 return content;
468 }
469 constexpr const char32_t * end() const noexcept {
470 return content + size();
471 }
472 constexpr char32_t operator[](size_t i) const noexcept {
473 return content[i];
474 }
475 template <size_t M> constexpr bool is_same_as(const fixed_string<M> & rhs) const noexcept {
476 if (real_size != rhs.size()) return false;
477 for (size_t i{0}; i != real_size; ++i) {
478 if (content[i] != rhs[i]) return false;
479 }
480 return true;
481 }
482 constexpr operator std::basic_string_view<char32_t>() const noexcept {
483 return std::basic_string_view<char32_t>{content, size()};
484 }
485};
486
487template <> class fixed_string<0> {
488 static constexpr char32_t empty[1] = {0};
489public:
490 template <typename T> constexpr fixed_string(const T *) noexcept {
491
492 }
493 constexpr fixed_string(std::initializer_list<char32_t>) noexcept {
494
495 }
496 constexpr fixed_string(const fixed_string &) noexcept {
497
498 }
499 constexpr bool correct() const noexcept {
500 return true;
501 }
502 constexpr size_t size() const noexcept {
503 return 0;
504 }
505 constexpr const char32_t * begin() const noexcept {
506 return empty;
507 }
508 constexpr const char32_t * end() const noexcept {
509 return empty + size();
510 }
511 constexpr char32_t operator[](size_t) const noexcept {
512 return 0;
513 }
514 constexpr operator std::basic_string_view<char32_t>() const noexcept {
515 return std::basic_string_view<char32_t>{empty, 0};
516 }
517};
518
519template <typename CharT, size_t N> fixed_string(const CharT (&)[N]) -> fixed_string<N-1>;
520template <typename CharT, size_t N> fixed_string(const std::array<CharT,N> &) -> fixed_string<N>;
521
522template <size_t N> fixed_string(fixed_string<N>) -> fixed_string<N>;
523
524}
525
526#endif

528#ifndef CTLL__TYPE_STACK__HPP

531namespace ctll {
532
533template <typename... Ts> struct list { };
534
535struct _nothing { };
536
537using empty_list = list<>;
538
539// calculate size of list content
540template <typename... Ts> constexpr auto size(list<Ts...>) noexcept { return sizeof...(Ts); }
541
542
543// check if the list is empty
544template <typename... Ts> constexpr bool empty(list<Ts...>) noexcept { return false; }
545constexpr bool empty(empty_list) { return true; }
546
547// concat two lists together left to right
548template <typename... As, typename... Bs> constexpr auto concat(list<As...>, list<Bs...>) noexcept -> list<As..., Bs...> { return {}; }
549
550// push something to the front of a list
551template <typename T, typename... As> constexpr auto push_front(T, list<As...>) noexcept -> list<T, As...> { return {}; }
552
553// pop element from the front of a list
554template <typename T, typename... As> constexpr auto pop_front(list<T, As...>) noexcept -> list<As...> { return {}; }
555constexpr auto pop_front(empty_list) -> empty_list;
556
557// pop element from the front of a list and return new typelist too
558template <typename Front, typename List> struct list_pop_pair {
559 Front front{};
560 List list{};
561 constexpr list_pop_pair() = default;
562};
563
564template <typename Head, typename... As, typename T = _nothing> constexpr auto pop_and_get_front(list<Head, As...>, T = T()) noexcept -> list_pop_pair<Head, list<As...>> { return {}; }
565template <typename T = _nothing> constexpr auto pop_and_get_front(empty_list, T = T()) noexcept -> list_pop_pair<T, empty_list> { return {}; }
566
567// return front of the list
568template <typename Head, typename... As, typename T = _nothing> constexpr auto front(list<Head, As...>, T = T()) noexcept -> Head { return {}; }
569template <typename T = _nothing> constexpr auto front(empty_list, T = T()) noexcept -> T { return {}; }
570
571// rotate list
572template <typename T> struct rotate_item {
573 template <typename... Ts> friend constexpr auto operator+(list<Ts...>, rotate_item<T>) noexcept -> list<T, Ts...> { return {}; }
574};
575
576template <typename... Ts> constexpr auto rotate(list<Ts...>) -> decltype((list<>{} + ... + rotate_item<Ts>{})) {
577 return {};
578}
579
580// set operations
581template <typename T> struct item_matcher {
582 struct not_selected {
583 template <typename... Ts> friend constexpr auto operator+(list<Ts...>, not_selected) -> list<Ts...>;
584 };
585 template <typename Y> struct wrapper {
586 template <typename... Ts> friend constexpr auto operator+(list<Ts...>, wrapper<Y>) -> list<Ts...,Y>;
587 };
588
589 static constexpr auto check(T) { return std::true_type{}; }
590 static constexpr auto check(...) { return std::false_type{}; }
591 static constexpr auto select(T) { return not_selected{}; }
592 template <typename Y> static constexpr auto select(Y) { return wrapper<Y>{}; }
593};
594
595template <typename T, typename... Ts> constexpr bool exists_in(T, list<Ts...>) noexcept {
596 return (item_matcher<T>::check(Ts{}) || ... || false);
597}
598
599template <typename T, typename... Ts> constexpr auto add_item(T item, list<Ts...> l) noexcept {
600 if constexpr (exists_in(item, l)) {
601 return l;
602 } else {
603 return list<Ts..., T>{};
604 }
605}
606
607template <typename T, typename... Ts> constexpr auto remove_item(T, list<Ts...>) noexcept {
608 item_matcher<T> matcher;
609 return decltype((list<>{} + ... + matcher.select(Ts{}))){};
610}
611
612}
613
614#endif

621// terminal type representing symbol / character of any type

623 static constexpr auto value = v;

626// epsilon = nothing on input tape
627// also used as an command for parsing means "do nothing"
628struct epsilon {
629 static constexpr auto value = '-';
630};
631
632// empty_stack_symbol = nothing on stack
633struct empty_stack_symbol {};
634
635// push<T...> is alias to list<T...>
636template <typename... Ts> using push = list<Ts...>;
637
638// accept/reject type for controlling output of LL1 machine
639struct accept { constexpr explicit operator bool() noexcept { return true; } };
640struct reject { constexpr explicit operator bool() noexcept { return false; } };
641
642// action type, every action item in grammar must inherit from
643struct action {
644 struct action_tag { };
645};
646
647// move one character forward and pop it from stack command
648struct pop_input {
649 struct pop_input_tag { };
650};
651
652// additional overloads for type list
653template <typename... Ts> constexpr auto push_front(pop_input, list<Ts...>) -> list<Ts...> { return {}; }
654
655template <typename... Ts> constexpr auto push_front(epsilon, list<Ts...>) -> list<Ts...> { return {}; }
656
657template <typename... As, typename... Bs> constexpr auto push_front(list<As...>, list<Bs...>) -> list<As..., Bs...> { return {}; }
658
659template <typename T, typename... As> constexpr auto pop_front_and_push_front(T item, list<As...> l) {
660 return push_front(item, pop_front(l));
661}
662
663// SPECIAL matching types for nicer grammars
664
665// match any term
666struct anything {
667 constexpr inline anything() noexcept { }
668 template <auto V> constexpr anything(term<V>) noexcept;
669};
670
671// match range of term A-B
672template <auto A, decltype(A) B> struct range {
673 constexpr inline range() noexcept { }
674 //template <auto V> constexpr range(term<V>) noexcept requires (A <= V) && (V <= B);
675 template <auto V, typename = std::enable_if_t<(A <= V) && (V <= B)>> constexpr range(term<V>) noexcept;
676};
677
678#ifdef __EDG__
679template <auto V, auto... Set> struct contains {
680 static constexpr bool value = ((Set == V) || ... || false);
681};
682#endif
683
684// match terms defined in set
685template <auto... Def> struct set {
686 constexpr inline set() noexcept { }
687 #ifdef __EDG__
688 template <auto V, typename = std::enable_if_t<contains<V, Def...>::value>> constexpr set(term<V>) noexcept;
689 #else
690 template <auto V, typename = std::enable_if_t<((Def == V) || ... || false)>> constexpr set(term<V>) noexcept;
691 #endif
692};
693
694// match terms not defined in set
695template <auto... Def> struct neg_set {
696 constexpr inline neg_set() noexcept { }
697
698 #ifdef __EDG__
699 template <auto V, typename = std::enable_if_t<!contains<V, Def...>::value>> constexpr neg_set(term<V>) noexcept;
700 #else
701 template <auto V, typename = std::enable_if_t<!((Def == V) || ... || false)>> constexpr neg_set(term<V>) noexcept;
702 #endif
703};
704
705// AUGMENTED grammar which completes user-defined grammar for all other cases
706template <typename Grammar> struct augment_grammar: public Grammar {
707 // start nonterminal is defined in parent type
708 using typename Grammar::_start;
709
710 // grammar rules are inherited from Grammar parent type
711 using Grammar::rule;
712
713 // term on stack and on input means pop_input;
714 template <auto A> static constexpr auto rule(term<A>, term<A>) -> ctll::pop_input;
715
716 // if the type on stack (range, set, neg_set, anything) is constructible from the terminal => pop_input
717 template <typename Expected, auto V> static constexpr auto rule(Expected, term<V>) -> std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible_v<Expected, term<V>>, ctll::pop_input>;
718
719 // empty stack and empty input means we are accepting
720 static constexpr auto rule(empty_stack_symbol, epsilon) -> ctll::accept;
721
722 // not matching anything else => reject
723 static constexpr auto rule(...) -> ctll::reject;
724
725 // start stack is just a list<Grammar::_start>;
726 using start_stack = list<typename Grammar::_start>;
727};
728
729}
730
731#endif
732
733#ifndef CTLL__ACTIONS__HPP
734#define CTLL__ACTIONS__HPP
735
736namespace ctll {
737 struct empty_subject { };
738
739 struct empty_actions {
740 // dummy operator so using Actions::operator() later will not give error
741 template <typename Action, typename InputSymbol, typename Subject> static constexpr auto apply(Action, InputSymbol, Subject subject) {
742 return subject;
743 }
744 };
745
746 template <typename Actions> struct identity: public Actions {
747 using Actions::apply;
748 // allow empty_subject to exists
749 template <typename Action, auto V> constexpr static auto apply(Action, term<V>, empty_subject) -> empty_subject { return {}; }
750 template <typename Action> constexpr static auto apply(Action, epsilon, empty_subject) -> empty_subject { return {}; }
751 };
752
753 template <typename Actions> struct ignore_unknown: public Actions {
754 using Actions::apply;
755 // allow flow thru unknown actions
756 template <typename Action, auto V, typename Subject> constexpr static auto apply(Action, term<V>, Subject) -> Subject { return {}; }
757 template <typename Action, typename Subject> constexpr static auto apply(Action, epsilon, Subject) -> Subject { return {}; }
758 };
759}
760
761#endif

763#ifndef CTLL_IN_A_MODULE
764#include <limits>
765#endif
766
767namespace ctll {
768
769enum class decision {
770 reject,
771 accept,
772 undecided
773};
774
775struct placeholder { };
776
777template <size_t> using index_placeholder = placeholder;
778
779#if CTLL_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
780template <typename Grammar, ctll::fixed_string input, typename ActionSelector = empty_actions, bool IgnoreUnknownActions = false> struct parser { // in c++20
781#else
782template <typename Grammar, const auto & input, typename ActionSelector = empty_actions, bool IgnoreUnknownActions = false> struct parser {
783#endif
784
785 #ifdef __GNUC__ // workaround to GCC bug
786 #if CTLL_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
787 static constexpr auto _input = input; // c++20 mode
788 #else
789 static constexpr auto & _input = input; // c++17 mode
790 #endif
791 #else
792 static constexpr auto _input = input; // everyone else
793 #endif
794
795 using Actions = ctll::conditional<IgnoreUnknownActions, ignore_unknown<ActionSelector>, identity<ActionSelector>>;
796 using grammar = augment_grammar<Grammar>;
797
798 template <size_t Pos, typename Stack, typename Subject, decision Decision> struct results {
799
800 static constexpr bool is_correct = Decision == decision::accept;
801
802 constexpr inline CTLL_FORCE_INLINE operator bool() const noexcept {
803 return is_correct;
804 }
805
806 #ifdef __GNUC__ // workaround to GCC bug
807 #if CTLL_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
808 static constexpr auto _input = input; // c++20 mode
809 #else
810 static constexpr auto & _input = input; // c++17 mode
811 #endif
812 #else
813 static constexpr auto _input = input; // everyone else
814 #endif
815
816 using output_type = Subject;
817 static constexpr size_t position = Pos;
818
819 constexpr auto operator+(placeholder) const noexcept {
820 if constexpr (Decision == decision::undecided) {
821 // parse for current char (RPos) with previous stack and subject :)
822 return parser<Grammar, _input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template decide<Pos, Stack, Subject>({}, {});
823 } else {
824 // if there is decision already => just push it to the end of fold expression
825 return *this;
826 }
827 }
828 };
829
830 template <size_t Pos> static constexpr auto get_current_term() noexcept {
831 if constexpr (Pos < input.size()) {
832 constexpr auto value = input[Pos];
833 if constexpr (value <= static_cast<decltype(value)>((std::numeric_limits<char>::max)())) {
834 return term<static_cast<char>(value)>{};
835 } else {
836 return term<value>{};
837 }
838
839 } else {
840 // return epsilon if we are past the input
841 return epsilon{};
842 }
843 }
844 template <size_t Pos> static constexpr auto get_previous_term() noexcept {
845 if constexpr (Pos == 0) {
846 // there is no previous character on input if we are on start
847 return epsilon{};
848 } else if constexpr ((Pos-1) < input.size()) {
849 constexpr auto value = input[Pos-1];
850 if constexpr (value <= static_cast<decltype(value)>((std::numeric_limits<char>::max)())) {
851 return term<static_cast<char>(value)>{};
852 } else {
853 return term<value>{};
854 }
855 } else {
856 return epsilon{};
857 }
858 }
859 // if rule is accept => return true and subject
860 template <size_t Pos, typename Terminal, typename Stack, typename Subject>
861 static constexpr auto move(ctll::accept, Terminal, Stack, Subject) noexcept {
862 return typename parser<Grammar, _input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos, Stack, Subject, decision::accept>();
863 }
864 // if rule is reject => return false and subject
865 template <size_t Pos, typename Terminal, typename Stack, typename Subject>
866 static constexpr auto move(ctll::reject, Terminal, Stack, Subject) noexcept {
867 return typename parser<Grammar, _input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos, Stack, Subject, decision::reject>();
868 }
869 // if rule is pop_input => move to next character
870 template <size_t Pos, typename Terminal, typename Stack, typename Subject>
871 static constexpr auto move(ctll::pop_input, Terminal, Stack, Subject) noexcept {
872 return typename parser<Grammar, _input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos+1, Stack, Subject, decision::undecided>();
873 }
874 // if rule is string => push it to the front of stack
875 template <size_t Pos, typename... Content, typename Terminal, typename Stack, typename Subject>
876 static constexpr auto move(push<Content...> string, Terminal, Stack stack, Subject subject) noexcept {
877 return decide<Pos>(push_front(string, stack), subject);
878 }
879 // if rule is epsilon (empty string) => continue
880 template <size_t Pos, typename Terminal, typename Stack, typename Subject>
881 static constexpr auto move(epsilon, Terminal, Stack stack, Subject subject) noexcept {
882 return decide<Pos>(stack, subject);
883 }
884 // if rule is string with current character at the beginning (term<V>) => move to next character
885 // and push string without the character (quick LL(1))
886 template <size_t Pos, auto V, typename... Content, typename Stack, typename Subject>
887 static constexpr auto move(push<term<V>, Content...>, term<V>, Stack stack, Subject) noexcept {
888 constexpr auto local_input = input;
889 return typename parser<Grammar, local_input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos+1, decltype(push_front(list<Content...>(), stack)), Subject, decision::undecided>();
890 }
891 // if rule is string with any character at the beginning (compatible with current term<T>) => move to next character
892 // and push string without the character (quick LL(1))
893 template <size_t Pos, auto V, typename... Content, auto T, typename Stack, typename Subject>
894 static constexpr auto move(push<anything, Content...>, term<T>, Stack stack, Subject) noexcept {
895 constexpr auto local_input = input;
896 return typename parser<Grammar, local_input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos+1, decltype(push_front(list<Content...>(), stack)), Subject, decision::undecided>();
897 }
898 // decide if we need to take action or move
899 template <size_t Pos, typename Stack, typename Subject> static constexpr auto decide(Stack previous_stack, Subject previous_subject) noexcept {
900 // each call means we pop something from stack
901 auto top_symbol = decltype(ctll::front(previous_stack, empty_stack_symbol()))();
902 // gcc pedantic warning
903 [[maybe_unused]] auto stack = decltype(ctll::pop_front(previous_stack))();
904
905 // in case top_symbol is action type (apply it on previous subject and get new one)
906 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<ctll::action, decltype(top_symbol)>) {
907 auto subject = Actions::apply(top_symbol, get_previous_term<Pos>(), previous_subject);
908
909 // in case that semantic action is error => reject input
910 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ctll::reject, decltype(subject)>) {
911 return typename parser<Grammar, _input, ActionSelector, IgnoreUnknownActions>::template results<Pos, Stack, Subject, decision::reject>();
912 } else {
913 return decide<Pos>(stack, subject);
914 }
915 } else {
916 // all other cases are ordinary for LL(1) parser
917 auto current_term = get_current_term<Pos>();
918 auto rule = decltype(grammar::rule(top_symbol,current_term))();
919 return move<Pos>(rule, current_term, stack, previous_subject);
920 }
921 }
922
923 // trampolines with folded expression
924 template <typename Subject, size_t... Pos> static constexpr auto trampoline_decide(Subject, std::index_sequence<Pos...>) noexcept {
925 // parse everything for first char and than for next and next ...
926 // Pos+1 is needed as we want to finish calculation with epsilons on stack
927 auto v = (decide<0, typename grammar::start_stack, Subject>({}, {}) + ... + index_placeholder<Pos+1>());
928 return v;
929 }
930
931 template <typename Subject = empty_subject> static constexpr auto trampoline_decide(Subject subject = {}) noexcept {
932 // there will be no recursion, just sequence long as the input
933 return trampoline_decide(subject, std::make_index_sequence<input.size()>());
934 }
935
936 template <typename Subject = empty_subject> using output = decltype(trampoline_decide<Subject>());
937 template <typename Subject = empty_subject> static inline constexpr bool correct_with = trampoline_decide<Subject>();
938
939};
940
941} // end of ctll namespace
942
943#endif
944
945#endif

1468#ifndef CTRE_V2__CTRE__FLAGS_AND_MODES__HPP
1469#define CTRE_V2__CTRE__FLAGS_AND_MODES__HPP
1470
1471namespace ctre {
1472
1473struct singleline { };
1474struct multiline { };
1475
1476struct case_sensitive { };
1477struct case_insensitive { };
1478
1479using ci = case_insensitive;
1480using cs = case_sensitive;
1481
1482template <typename... Flags> struct flag_list { };
1483
1484struct flags {
1485 bool block_empty_match = false;
1486 bool multiline = false;
1487 bool case_insensitive = false;
1488
1489 constexpr flags() = default;
1490 constexpr flags(const flags &) = default;
1491 constexpr flags(flags &&) = default;
1492
1493 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE flags(ctre::singleline v) noexcept { set_flag(v); }
1494 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE flags(ctre::multiline v) noexcept { set_flag(v); }
1495 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE flags(ctre::case_sensitive v) noexcept { set_flag(v); }
1496 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE flags(ctre::case_insensitive v) noexcept { set_flag(v); }
1497
1498
1499 template <typename... Args> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE flags(ctll::list<Args...>) noexcept {
1500 (this->set_flag(Args{}), ...);
1501 }
1502
1503 constexpr friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto operator+(flags f, pcre::mode_case_insensitive) noexcept {
1504 f.case_insensitive = true;
1505 return f;
1506 }
1507
1508 constexpr friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto operator+(flags f, pcre::mode_case_sensitive) noexcept {
1509 f.case_insensitive = false;
1510 return f;
1511 }
1512
1513 constexpr friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto operator+(flags f, pcre::mode_singleline) noexcept {
1514 f.multiline = false;
1515 return f;
1516 }
1517
1518 constexpr friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto operator+(flags f, pcre::mode_multiline) noexcept {
1519 f.multiline = true;
1520 return f;
1521 }
1522
1523 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void set_flag(ctre::singleline) noexcept {
1524 multiline = false;
1525 }
1526
1527 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void set_flag(ctre::multiline) noexcept {
1528 multiline = true;
1529 }
1530
1531 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void set_flag(ctre::case_insensitive) noexcept {
1532 case_insensitive = true;
1533 }
1534
1535 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void set_flag(ctre::case_sensitive) noexcept {
1536 case_insensitive = false;
1537 }
1538};
1539
1540constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto not_empty_match(flags f) {
1541 f.block_empty_match = true;
1542 return f;
1543}
1544
1545constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto consumed_something(flags f, bool condition = true) {
1546 if (condition) f.block_empty_match = false;
1547 return f;
1548}
1549
1550constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool cannot_be_empty_match(flags f) {
1551 return f.block_empty_match;
1552}
1553
1554constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool multiline_mode(flags f) {
1555 return f.multiline;
1556}
1557
1558constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool is_case_insensitive(flags f) {
1559 return f.case_insensitive;
1560}
1561
1562} // namespace ctre

1570namespace ctre {
1571
1572// sfinae check for types here
1573
1574template <typename T> class MatchesCharacter {
1575 template <typename Y, typename CharT> static auto test(CharT c) -> decltype(Y::match_char(c, std::declval<const flags &>()), std::true_type());
1576 template <typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
1577public:
1578 template <typename CharT> static inline constexpr bool value = decltype(test<T>(std::declval<CharT>()))();
1579};
1580
1581template <typename T> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool is_ascii_alpha(T v) {
1582 return ((v >= static_cast<T>('a') && v <= static_cast<T>('z')) || (v >= static_cast<T>('A') && v <= static_cast<T>('Z')));
1583}
1584
1585template <typename T> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool is_ascii_alpha_lowercase(T v) {
1586 return (v >= static_cast<T>('a')) && (v <= static_cast<T>('z'));
1587}
1588
1589template <typename T> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool is_ascii_alpha_uppercase(T v) {
1590 return (v >= static_cast<T>('A')) && v <= (static_cast<T>('Z'));
1591}
1592
1593template <auto V> struct character {
1594 template <typename CharT> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool match_char(CharT value, const flags & f) noexcept {
1595 if constexpr (is_ascii_alpha(V)) {
1596 if (is_case_insensitive(f)) {
1597 if (value == (V ^ static_cast<decltype(V)>(0x20))) {
1598 return true;//
1599 }
1600 }
1601 }
1602 return value == V;
1603 }
1604};
1605
1606template <typename... Content> struct negative_set {
1607 template <typename CharT> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool match_char(CharT value, const flags & f) noexcept {
1608 return !(Content::match_char(value, f) || ... || false);
1609 }
1610};
1611
1612template <typename... Content> struct set {
1613 template <typename CharT> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool match_char(CharT value, const flags & f) noexcept {
1614 return (Content::match_char(value, f) || ... || false);
1615 }
1616};
1617
1618template <auto... Cs> struct enumeration : set<character<Cs>...> { };
1619
1620template <typename... Content> struct negate {
1621 template <typename CharT> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool match_char(CharT value, const flags & f) noexcept {
1622 return !(Content::match_char(value, f) || ... || false);
1623 }
1624};
1625
1626template <auto A, auto B> struct char_range {
1627 template <typename CharT> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool match_char(CharT value, const flags & f) noexcept {
1628 if constexpr (is_ascii_alpha_lowercase(A) && is_ascii_alpha_lowercase(B)) {
1629 if (is_case_insensitive(f)) {
1630 if (value >= (A ^ static_cast<decltype(A)>(0x20)) && value <= (B ^ static_cast<decltype(B)>(0x20))) {
1631 return true;//
1632 }
1633 }
1634 } else if constexpr (is_ascii_alpha_uppercase(A) && is_ascii_alpha_uppercase(B)) {
1635 if (is_case_insensitive(f)) {
1636 if (value >= (A ^ static_cast<decltype(A)>(0x20)) && value <= (B ^ static_cast<decltype(B)>(0x20))) {
1637 return true;//
1638 }
1639 }
1640 }
1641 return (value >= A) && (value <= B);
1642 }
1643};
1644using word_chars = set<char_range<'A','Z'>, char_range<'a','z'>, char_range<'0','9'>, character<'_'> >;
1645
1646using space_chars = enumeration<' ', '\t', '\n', '\v', '\f', '\r'>;
1647
1648using vertical_space_chars = enumeration<
1649 char{0x000A}, // Linefeed (LF)
1650 char{0x000B}, // Vertical tab (VT)
1651 char{0x000C}, // Form feed (FF)
1652 char{0x000D}, // Carriage return (CR)
1653 char32_t{0x0085}, // Next line (NEL)
1654 char32_t{0x2028}, // Line separator
1655 char32_t{0x2029} // Paragraph separator
1656>;
1657
1658using horizontal_space_chars = enumeration<
1659 char{0x0009}, // Horizontal tab (HT)
1660 char{0x0020}, // Space
1661 char32_t{0x00A0}, // Non-break space
1662 char32_t{0x1680}, // Ogham space mark
1663 char32_t{0x180E}, // Mongolian vowel separator
1664 char32_t{0x2000}, // En quad
1665 char32_t{0x2001}, // Em quad
1666 char32_t{0x2002}, // En space
1667 char32_t{0x2003}, // Em space
1668 char32_t{0x2004}, // Three-per-em space
1669 char32_t{0x2005}, // Four-per-em space
1670 char32_t{0x2006}, // Six-per-em space
1671 char32_t{0x2007}, // Figure space
1672 char32_t{0x2008}, // Punctuation space
1673 char32_t{0x2009}, // Thin space
1674 char32_t{0x200A}, // Hair space
1675 char32_t{0x202F}, // Narrow no-break space
1676 char32_t{0x205F}, // Medium mathematical space
1677 char32_t{0x3000} // Ideographic space
1678>;
1679
1680using alphanum_chars = set<char_range<'A','Z'>, char_range<'a','z'>, char_range<'0','9'> >;
1681
1682using alpha_chars = set<char_range<'A','Z'>, char_range<'a','z'> >;
1683
1684using xdigit_chars = set<char_range<'A','F'>, char_range<'a','f'>, char_range<'0','9'> >;
1685
1686using punct_chars
1687 = enumeration<'!', '"', '#', '$', '%', '&', '\'', '(', ')', '*', '+', ',', '-',
1688 '.', '/', ':', ';', '<', '=', '>', '?', '@', '[', '\\', ']',
1689 '^', '_', '`', '{', '|', '}', '~'>;
1690
1691using digit_chars = char_range<'0','9'>;
1692
1693using ascii_chars = char_range<'\x00','\x7F'>;
1694
1695}
1696
1697#endif

1883// properties name & value
1884
1885template <auto... Str> struct property_name { };
1886template <auto... Str> struct property_value { };

1888template <size_t Sz> constexpr std::string_view get_string_view(const char (& arr)[Sz]) noexcept {
1889 return std::string_view(arr, Sz);
1890}
1891
1892// basic support for binary and type-value properties
1893
1894template <typename T, T Type> struct binary_property;
1895template <typename T, T Type, auto Value> struct property;
1896
1897template <auto Type> using make_binary_property = binary_property<std::remove_const_t<decltype(Type)>, Type>;
1898template <auto Type, auto Value> using make_property = property<std::remove_const_t<decltype(Type)>, Type, Value>;
1899
1900// unicode TS#18 level 1.2 general_category
1901template <uni::detail::binary_prop Property> struct binary_property<uni::detail::binary_prop, Property> {
1902 template <typename CharT> inline static constexpr bool match_char(CharT c, const flags &) noexcept {
1903 return uni::detail::get_binary_prop<Property>(static_cast<char32_t>(c));
1904 }
1905};
1906
1907// unicode TS#18 level 1.2.2
1908
1909enum class property_type {
1910 script, script_extension, age, block, unknown
1911};
1912
1913// unicode TS#18 level 1.2.2
1914
1915template <uni::script Script> struct binary_property<uni::script, Script> {
1916 template <typename CharT> inline static constexpr bool match_char(CharT c, const flags &) noexcept {
1917 return uni::cp_script(c) == Script;
1918 }
1919};
1920
1921template <uni::script Script> struct property<property_type, property_type::script_extension, Script> {
1922 template <typename CharT> inline static constexpr bool match_char(CharT c, const flags &) noexcept {
1923 for (uni::script sc: uni::cp_script_extensions(c)) {
1924 if (sc == Script) return true;
1925 }
1926 return false;
1927 }
1928};
1929
1930template <uni::version Age> struct binary_property<uni::version, Age> {
1931 template <typename CharT> inline static constexpr bool match_char(CharT c, const flags &) noexcept {
1932 return uni::cp_age(c) <= Age;
1933 }
1934};
1935
1936template <uni::block Block> struct binary_property<uni::block, Block> {
1937 template <typename CharT> inline static constexpr bool match_char(CharT c, const flags &) noexcept {
1938 return uni::cp_block(c) == Block;
1939 }
1940};
1941
1942// nonbinary properties
1943
1944template <typename = void> // Make it always a template as propnamecomp isn't defined yet
1945constexpr property_type property_type_from_name(std::string_view str) noexcept {
1946 using namespace std::string_view_literals;
1947 if (uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "script"sv) == 0 || uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "sc"sv) == 0) {
1948 return property_type::script;
1949 } else if (uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "script_extension"sv) == 0 || uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "scx"sv) == 0) {
1950 return property_type::script_extension;
1951 } else if (uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "age"sv) == 0) {
1952 return property_type::age;
1953 } else if (uni::detail::propnamecomp(str, "block"sv) == 0) {
1954 return property_type::block;
1955 } else {
1956 return property_type::unknown;
1957 }
1958}
1959
1960template <property_type Property> struct property_type_builder {
1961 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
1962 return ctll::reject{};
1963 }
1964};
1965
1966template <auto... Name> struct property_builder {
1967 static constexpr char name[sizeof...(Name)]{static_cast<char>(Name)...};
1968 static constexpr property_type type = property_type_from_name(get_string_view(name));
1969
1970 using helper = property_type_builder<type>;
1971
1972 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
1973 return helper::template get<Value...>();
1974 }
1975};
1976
1977// unicode TS#18 level 1.2.2 script support
1978
1979template <> struct property_type_builder<property_type::script> {
1980 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
1981 constexpr char value[sizeof...(Value)]{static_cast<char>(Value)...};
1982 constexpr auto sc = uni::detail::script_from_string(get_string_view(value));
1983 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unknown(sc)) {
1984 return ctll::reject{};
1985 } else {
1986 return make_binary_property<sc>();
1987 }
1988 }
1989};
1990
1991template <> struct property_type_builder<property_type::script_extension> {
1992 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
1993 constexpr char value[sizeof...(Value)]{static_cast<char>(Value)...};
1994 constexpr auto sc = uni::detail::script_from_string(get_string_view(value));
1995 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unknown(sc)) {
1996 return ctll::reject{};
1997 } else {
1998 return make_property<property_type::script_extension, sc>();
1999 }
2000 }
2001};
2002
2003template <> struct property_type_builder<property_type::age> {
2004 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
2005 constexpr char value[sizeof...(Value)]{static_cast<char>(Value)...};
2006 constexpr auto age = uni::detail::age_from_string(get_string_view(value));
2007 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unassigned(age)) {
2008 return ctll::reject{};
2009 } else {
2010 return make_binary_property<age>();
2011 }
2012 }
2013};
2014
2015template <> struct property_type_builder<property_type::block> {
2016 template <auto... Value> static constexpr auto get() {
2017 constexpr char value[sizeof...(Value)]{static_cast<char>(Value)...};
2018 constexpr auto block = uni::detail::block_from_string(get_string_view(value));
2019 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unknown(block)) {
2020 return ctll::reject{};
2021 } else {
2022 return make_binary_property<block>();
2023 }
2024 }
2025};

2027}

2132template <auto... Name> struct id {
2133 static constexpr auto name = ctll::fixed_string<sizeof...(Name)>{{Name...}};
2134
2135 friend constexpr auto operator==(id<Name...>, id<Name...>) noexcept -> std::true_type { return {}; }
2136
2137 template <auto... Other> friend constexpr auto operator==(id<Name...>, id<Other...>) noexcept -> std::false_type { return {}; }
2138
2139 template <typename T> friend constexpr auto operator==(id<Name...>, T) noexcept -> std::false_type { return {}; }
2140
2141 template <typename T> friend constexpr auto operator==(T, id<Name...>) noexcept -> std::false_type { return {}; }
2142};

2155template <size_t Counter> struct pcre_parameters {
2156 static constexpr size_t current_counter = Counter;
2157};
2158
2159template <typename Stack = ctll::list<>, typename Parameters = pcre_parameters<0>, typename Mode = ctll::list<>> struct pcre_context {
2160 using stack_type = Stack;
2161 using parameters_type = Parameters;
2162 using mode_list = Mode;
2163 static constexpr inline auto stack = stack_type();
2164 static constexpr inline auto parameters = parameters_type();
2165 static constexpr inline auto mode = mode_list();
2166 constexpr pcre_context() noexcept { }
2167 constexpr pcre_context(Stack, Parameters) noexcept { }
2168 constexpr pcre_context(Stack, Parameters, Mode) noexcept { }
2169};
2170
2171template <typename... Content, typename Parameters> pcre_context(ctll::list<Content...>, Parameters) -> pcre_context<ctll::list<Content...>, Parameters>;
2172
2173template <size_t Value> struct number { };
2174
2175template <size_t Id> struct capture_id { };

2229#ifndef CTRE__ACTIONS__BACKREFERENCE__HPP
2230#define CTRE__ACTIONS__BACKREFERENCE__HPP
2231
2232// backreference with name
2233template <auto... Str, auto V, typename... Ts, size_t Counter> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_back_reference, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<id<Str...>, Ts...>, pcre_parameters<Counter>>) {
2234 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(back_reference_with_name<id<Str...>>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), pcre_parameters<Counter>()};
2235}
2236
2237// with just a number
2238template <auto V, size_t Id, typename... Ts, size_t Counter> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_back_reference, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<number<Id>, Ts...>, pcre_parameters<Counter>>) {
2239 // if we are looking outside of existing list of Ids ... reject input during parsing
2240 if constexpr (Counter < Id) {
2241 return ctll::reject{};
2242 } else {
2243 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(back_reference<Id>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), pcre_parameters<Counter>()};
2244 }
2245}
2246
2247// relative backreference
2248template <auto V, size_t Id, typename... Ts, size_t Counter> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_relative_back_reference, ctll::term<V>, [[maybe_unused]] pcre_context<ctll::list<number<Id>, Ts...>, pcre_parameters<Counter>>) {
2249 // if we are looking outside of existing list of Ids ... reject input during parsing
2250 if constexpr (Counter < Id) {
2251 return ctll::reject{};
2252 } else {
2253 constexpr size_t absolute_id = (Counter + 1) - Id;
2254 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(back_reference<absolute_id>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), pcre_parameters<Counter>()};
2255 }
2256}

2409#ifndef CTRE__ACTIONS__FUSION__HPP
2410#define CTRE__ACTIONS__FUSION__HPP
2411
2412static constexpr size_t combine_max_repeat_length(size_t A, size_t B) {
2413 if (A && B) return A+B;
2414 else return 0;
2415}
2416
2417template <size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content> static constexpr auto combine_repeat(repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>) {
2418 return repeat<MinA + MinB, combine_max_repeat_length(MaxA, MaxB), Content...>();
2419}
2420
2421template <size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content> static constexpr auto combine_repeat(lazy_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, lazy_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>) {
2422 return lazy_repeat<MinA + MinB, combine_max_repeat_length(MaxA, MaxB), Content...>();
2423}
2424
2425template <size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content> static constexpr auto combine_repeat(possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, possessive_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>) {
2426 [[maybe_unused]] constexpr bool first_is_unbounded = (MaxA == 0);
2427 [[maybe_unused]] constexpr bool second_is_nonempty = (MinB > 0);
2428 [[maybe_unused]] constexpr bool second_can_be_empty = (MinB == 0);
2429
2430 if constexpr (first_is_unbounded && second_is_nonempty) {
2431 // will always reject, but I keep the content, so I have some amount of captures
2432 return sequence<reject, Content...>();
2433 } else if constexpr (first_is_unbounded) {
2434 return possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>();
2435 } else if constexpr (second_can_be_empty) {
2436 return possessive_repeat<MinA, combine_max_repeat_length(MaxA, MaxB), Content...>();
2437 } else {
2438 return possessive_repeat<MaxA + MinB, combine_max_repeat_length(MaxA, MaxB), Content...>();
2439 }
2440}
2441
2442// concat repeat sequences
2443template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2444 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(combine_repeat(repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>(), repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>()), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2445}
2446
2447// concat lazy repeat sequences
2448template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<lazy_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, lazy_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2449 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(combine_repeat(lazy_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>(), lazy_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>()), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2450}
2451
2452// concat possessive repeat seqeunces
2453template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<possessive_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2454 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(combine_repeat(possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>(), possessive_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>()), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2455}
2456
2457// concat repeat sequences into sequence
2458template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... As, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<sequence<repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, As...>,repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>,Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2459 using result = decltype(combine_repeat(repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>(), repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>()));
2460
2461 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(sequence<result,As...>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2462}
2463
2464// concat lazy repeat sequences into sequence
2465template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... As, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<sequence<lazy_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, As...>,lazy_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>,Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2466 using result = decltype(combine_repeat(lazy_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>(), lazy_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>()));
2467
2468 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(sequence<result,As...>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2469}
2470
2471// concat possessive repeat sequences into sequence
2472template <auto V, size_t MinA, size_t MaxA, size_t MinB, size_t MaxB, typename... Content, typename... As, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_sequence, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<sequence<possessive_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>, As...>,possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>,Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2473 using result = decltype(combine_repeat(possessive_repeat<MinB, MaxB, Content...>(), possessive_repeat<MinA, MaxA, Content...>()));
2474
2475 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(sequence<result,As...>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2476}

2480#ifndef CTRE__ACTIONS__HEXDEC__HPP
2481#define CTRE__ACTIONS__HEXDEC__HPP
2482
2483// hexdec character support (seed)
2484template <auto V, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::create_hexdec, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2485 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(number<0ull>(), subject.stack), subject.parameters};
2486}
2487// hexdec character support (push value)
2488template <auto V, size_t N, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::push_hexdec, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<number<N>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2489 constexpr auto previous = N << 4ull;
2490 if constexpr (V >= 'a' && V <= 'f') {
2491 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(number<(previous + (V - 'a' + 10))>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2492 } else if constexpr (V >= 'A' && V <= 'F') {
2493 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(number<(previous + (V - 'A' + 10))>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2494 } else {
2495 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(number<(previous + (V - '0'))>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2496 }
2497}
2498// hexdec character support (convert to character)
2499template <auto V, size_t N, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::finish_hexdec, ctll::term<V>, pcre_context<ctll::list<number<N>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2500 constexpr size_t max_char = (std::numeric_limits<char>::max)();
2501 if constexpr (N <= max_char) {
2502 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(character<char{N}>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2503 } else {
2504 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(character<char32_t{N}>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2505 }
2506}

2510#ifndef CTRE__ACTIONS__LOOKAHEAD__HPP
2511#define CTRE__ACTIONS__LOOKAHEAD__HPP
2512
2513// lookahead positive start

2714
2715// make_property
2716template <auto V, auto... Name, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_property, ctll::term<V>, [[maybe_unused]] pcre_context<ctll::list<property_name<Name...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2717 //return ctll::reject{};
2718 constexpr char name[sizeof...(Name)]{static_cast<char>(Name)...};
2719 constexpr auto p = uni::detail::binary_prop_from_string(get_string_view(name));
2720
2721 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unknown(p)) {
2722 return ctll::reject{};
2723 } else {
2724 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(make_binary_property<p>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2725 }
2726}
2727
2728// make_property
2729template <auto V, auto... Value, auto... Name, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_property, ctll::term<V>, [[maybe_unused]] pcre_context<ctll::list<property_value<Value...>, property_name<Name...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2730 //return ctll::reject{};
2731 constexpr auto prop = property_builder<Name...>::template get<Value...>();
2732
2733 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<decltype(prop), ctll::reject>) {
2734 return ctll::reject{};
2735 } else {
2736 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(prop, ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2737 }
2738}
2739
2740// make_property_negative
2741template <auto V, auto... Name, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_property_negative, ctll::term<V>, [[maybe_unused]] pcre_context<ctll::list<property_name<Name...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2742 //return ctll::reject{};
2743 constexpr char name[sizeof...(Name)]{static_cast<char>(Name)...};
2744 constexpr auto p = uni::detail::binary_prop_from_string(get_string_view(name));
2745
2746 if constexpr (uni::detail::is_unknown(p)) {
2747 return ctll::reject{};
2748 } else {
2749 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(negate<make_binary_property<p>>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2750 }
2751}
2752
2753// make_property_negative
2754template <auto V, auto... Value, auto... Name, typename... Ts, typename Parameters> static constexpr auto apply(pcre::make_property_negative, ctll::term<V>, [[maybe_unused]] pcre_context<ctll::list<property_value<Value...>, property_name<Name...>, Ts...>, Parameters> subject) {
2755 //return ctll::reject{};
2756 constexpr auto prop = property_builder<Name...>::template get<Value...>();
2757
2758 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<decltype(prop), ctll::reject>) {
2759 return ctll::reject{};
2760 } else {
2761 return pcre_context{ctll::push_front(negate<decltype(prop)>(), ctll::list<Ts...>()), subject.parameters};
2762 }
2763}

3102struct utf8_iterator {
3103 using self_type = utf8_iterator;
3104 using value_type = char8_t;
3105 using reference = char8_t;
3106 using pointer = const char8_t *;
3107 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
3108 using difference_type = int;
3109
3110 struct sentinel {
3111 // this is here only because I want to support std::make_reverse_iterator
3112 using self_type = sentinel;
3113 using value_type = char8_t;
3114 using reference = char8_t &;
3115 using pointer = const char8_t *;
3116 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
3117 using difference_type = int;
3118
3119 // it's just sentinel it won't be ever called
3120 auto operator++() noexcept -> self_type &;
3121 auto operator++(int) noexcept -> self_type;
3122 auto operator--() noexcept -> self_type &;
3123 auto operator--(int) noexcept -> self_type;
3124 friend auto operator==(self_type, self_type) noexcept -> bool;
3125 auto operator*() noexcept -> reference;
3126
3127 friend constexpr auto operator==(self_type, const char8_t * other_ptr) noexcept {
3128 return *other_ptr == char8_t{0};
3129 }
3130
3131 friend constexpr auto operator!=(self_type, const char8_t * other_ptr) noexcept {
3132 return *other_ptr != char8_t{0};
3133 }
3134
3135#if __cpp_impl_three_way_comparison < 201907L
3136 friend constexpr auto operator==(const char8_t * other_ptr, self_type) noexcept {
3137 return *other_ptr == char8_t{0};
3138 }
3139
3140 friend constexpr auto operator!=(const char8_t * other_ptr, self_type) noexcept {
3141 return *other_ptr != char8_t{0};
3142 }
3143#endif
3144 };
3145
3146 const char8_t * ptr{nullptr};
3147 const char8_t * end{nullptr};
3148
3149 constexpr friend bool operator!=(const utf8_iterator & lhs, sentinel) {
3150 return lhs.ptr < lhs.end;
3151 }
3152
3153 constexpr friend bool operator!=(const utf8_iterator & lhs, const char8_t * rhs) {
3154 return lhs.ptr != rhs;
3155 }
3156
3157 constexpr friend bool operator!=(const utf8_iterator & lhs, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3158 return lhs.ptr != rhs.ptr;
3159 }
3160
3161 constexpr friend bool operator==(const utf8_iterator & lhs, sentinel) {
3162 return lhs.ptr >= lhs.end;
3163 }
3164
3165 constexpr friend bool operator==(const utf8_iterator & lhs, const char8_t * rhs) {
3166 return lhs.ptr == rhs;
3167 }
3168
3169 constexpr friend bool operator==(const utf8_iterator & lhs, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3170 return lhs.ptr == rhs.ptr;
3171 }
3172
3173#if __cpp_impl_three_way_comparison < 201907L
3174 constexpr friend bool operator!=(sentinel, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3175 return rhs.ptr < rhs.end;
3176 }
3177
3178 constexpr friend bool operator!=(const char8_t * lhs, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3179 return lhs == rhs.ptr;
3180 }
3181
3182 constexpr friend bool operator==(sentinel, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3183 return rhs.ptr >= rhs.end;
3184 }
3185
3186 constexpr friend bool operator==(const char8_t * lhs, const utf8_iterator & rhs) {
3187 return lhs == rhs.ptr;
3188 }
3189#endif
3190
3191
3192 constexpr utf8_iterator & operator=(const char8_t * rhs) {
3193 ptr = rhs;
3194 return *this;
3195 }
3196
3197 constexpr operator const char8_t *() const noexcept {
3198 return ptr;
3199 }
3200
3201 constexpr utf8_iterator & operator++() noexcept {
3202 // the contant is mapping from first 5 bits of first code unit to length of UTF8 code point -1
3203 // xxxxx -> yy (5 bits to 2 bits)
3204 // 5 bits are 32 combination, and for each I need 2 bits, hence 64 bit constant
3205 // (*ptr >> 2) & 0b111110 look at the left 5 bits ignoring the least significant
3206 // & 0b11u selects only needed two bits
3207 // +1 because each iteration is at least one code unit forward
3208
3209 ptr += ((0x3A55000000000000ull >> ((*ptr >> 2) & 0b111110u)) & 0b11u) + 1;
3210 return *this;
3211 }
3212
3213 constexpr utf8_iterator & operator--() noexcept {
3214 if (ptr > end) {
3215 ptr = end-1;
3216 } else {
3217 --ptr;
3218 }
3219
3220 while ((*ptr & 0b11000000u) == 0b10'000000) {
3221 --ptr;
3222 }
3223
3224 return *this;
3225 }
3226
3227 constexpr utf8_iterator operator--(int) noexcept {
3228 auto self = *this;
3229 this->operator--();
3230 return self;
3231 }
3232
3233 constexpr utf8_iterator operator++(int) noexcept {
3234 auto self = *this;
3235 this->operator++();
3236 return self;
3237 }
3238
3239 constexpr utf8_iterator operator+(unsigned step) const noexcept {
3240 utf8_iterator result = *this;
3241 while (step > 0) {
3242 ++result;
3243 step--;
3244 }
3245 return result;
3246 }
3247
3248 constexpr utf8_iterator operator-(unsigned step) const noexcept {
3249 utf8_iterator result = *this;
3250 while (step > 0) {
3251 --result;
3252 step--;
3253 }
3254 return result;
3255 }
3256
3257 constexpr char32_t operator*() const noexcept {
3258 constexpr char32_t mojibake = 0xFFFDull;
3259
3260 // quickpath
3261 if (!(*ptr & 0b1000'0000u)) CTRE_LIKELY {
3262 return *ptr;
3263 }
3264
3265 // calculate length based on first 5 bits
3266 const unsigned length = ((0x3A55000000000000ull >> ((*ptr >> 2) & 0b111110u)) & 0b11u);
3267
3268 // actual length is number + 1 bytes
3269
3270 // length 0 here means it's a bad front unit
3271 if (!length) CTRE_UNLIKELY {
3272 return mojibake;
3273 }
3274
3275 // if part of the utf-8 sequence is past the end
3276 if (((ptr + length) >= end)) CTRE_UNLIKELY {
3277 return mojibake;
3278 }
3279
3280 if ((ptr[1] & 0b1100'0000u) != 0b1000'0000) CTRE_UNLIKELY {
3281 return mojibake;
3282 }
3283
3284 const char8_t mask = static_cast<char8_t>(0b0011'1111u >> length);
3285
3286 // length = 1 (2 bytes) mask = 0b0001'1111u
3287 // length = 2 (3 bytes) mask = 0b0000'1111u
3288 // length = 3 (4 bytes) mask = 0b0000'0111u
3289
3290 // remove utf8 front bits, get only significant part
3291 // and add first trailing unit
3292
3293 char32_t result = static_cast<char32_t>((ptr[0] & mask) << 6u) | (ptr[1] & 0b0011'1111u);
3294
3295 // add rest of trailing units
3296 if (length == 1) CTRE_LIKELY {
3297 return result;
3298 }
3299
3300 if ((ptr[2] & 0b1100'0000u) != 0b1000'0000) CTRE_UNLIKELY {
3301 return mojibake;
3302 }
3303
3304 result = (result << 6) | (ptr[2] & 0b0011'1111u);
3305
3306 if (length == 2) CTRE_LIKELY {
3307 return result;
3308 }
3309
3310 if ((ptr[3] & 0b1100'0000u) != 0b1000'0000) CTRE_UNLIKELY {
3311 return mojibake;
3312 }
3313
3314 return (result << 6) | (ptr[3] & 0b0011'1111u);
3315 }
3316};

3325 }

3327 return utf8_iterator::sentinel{};

3372template <size_t Id, typename Name = void> struct captured_content {
3373 template <typename Iterator> class storage {
3374 Iterator _begin{};
3375 Iterator _end{};
3376
3377 bool _matched{false};
3378 public:
3379 using char_type = typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::value_type;
3380
3381 using name = Name;
3382
3383 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE storage() noexcept {}
3384
3385 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void matched() noexcept {
3386 _matched = true;
3387 }
3388 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void unmatch() noexcept {
3389 _matched = false;
3390 }
3391 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void set_start(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3392 _begin = pos;
3393 }
3394 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE storage & set_end(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3395 _end = pos;
3396 return *this;
3397 }
3398 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE Iterator get_end() const noexcept {
3399 return _end;
3400 }
3401
3402
3403 constexpr auto begin() const noexcept {
3404 return _begin;
3405 }
3406 constexpr auto end() const noexcept {
3407 return _end;
3408 }
3409
3410 constexpr explicit CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator bool() const noexcept {
3411 return _matched;
3412 }
3413
3414 template <typename It = Iterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE const auto * data_unsafe() const noexcept {
3415 static_assert(!is_reverse_iterator<It>, "Iterator in your capture must not be reverse!");
3416
3417 #if __cpp_char8_t >= 201811
3418 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Iterator, utf8_iterator>) {
3419 return _begin.ptr;
3420 } else { // I'm doing this to avoid warning about dead code
3421 #endif
3422
3423 #ifdef _MSC_VER
3424 return std::to_address(_begin); // I'm enabling this only for MSVC for now, as some clang old versions with various libraries (random combinations) has different problems
3425 #else
3426 return &*_begin;
3427 #endif
3428
3429 #if __cpp_char8_t >= 201811
3430 }
3431 #endif
3432 }
3433
3434 template <typename It = Iterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE const auto * data() const noexcept {
3435 constexpr bool must_be_contiguous_nonreverse_iterator = is_random_accessible<typename std::iterator_traits<It>::iterator_category> && !is_reverse_iterator<It>;
3436
3437 static_assert(must_be_contiguous_nonreverse_iterator, "To access result as a pointer you need to provide a random access iterator/range to regex (which is not reverse iterator based).");
3438
3439 return data_unsafe();
3440 }
3441
3442 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto size() const noexcept {
3443 return static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(begin(), end()));
3444 }
3445
3446 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE size_t unit_size() const noexcept {
3447 #if __cpp_char8_t >= 201811
3448 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Iterator, utf8_iterator>) {
3449 return static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(_begin.ptr, _end.ptr));
3450 } else {
3451 return static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(begin(), end()));
3452 }
3453 #else
3454 return static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(begin(), end()));
3455 #endif
3456 }
3457
3458#if __has_include(<charconv>)
3459 template <typename R = int, typename... Ts> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_number(Ts && ... args) const noexcept -> R {
3460 R result{0};
3461 const auto view = to_view();
3462 std::from_chars(view.data(), view.data() + view.size(), result, std::forward<Ts>(args)...);
3463 return result;
3464 }
3465
3466 template <typename R = int, typename... Ts> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_number(Ts && ... args) const noexcept -> std::optional<R> {
3467 if (!static_cast<bool>(*this)) {
3468 return std::nullopt;
3469 }
3470
3471 return to_number<R>(std::forward<Ts>(args)...);
3472 }
3473#endif
3474
3475 template <typename It = Iterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_view() const noexcept {
3476 // random access, because C++ (waving hands around)
3477 constexpr bool must_be_nonreverse_contiguous_iterator = is_random_accessible<typename std::iterator_traits<std::remove_const_t<It>>::iterator_category> && !is_reverse_iterator<It>;
3478
3479 static_assert(must_be_nonreverse_contiguous_iterator, "To convert capture into a basic_string_view you need to provide a pointer or a contiguous non-reverse iterator/range to regex.");
3480
3481 return std::basic_string_view<char_type>(data_unsafe(), static_cast<size_t>(unit_size()));
3482 }
3483
3484 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto view() const noexcept {
3485 return to_view();
3486 }
3487
3488 template <typename It = Iterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_view() const noexcept -> std::optional<std::basic_string_view<char_type>> {
3489 if (!static_cast<bool>(*this)) {
3490 return std::nullopt;
3491 }
3492 return to_view();
3493 }
3494
3495 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE std::basic_string<char_type> to_string() const noexcept {
3496 #if __cpp_char8_t >= 201811
3497 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Iterator, utf8_iterator>) {
3498 return std::basic_string<char_type>(data_unsafe(), static_cast<size_t>(unit_size()));
3499 } else {
3500 return std::basic_string<char_type>(begin(), end());
3501 }
3502 #else
3503 return std::basic_string<char_type>(begin(), end());
3504 #endif
3505 }
3506
3507 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto str() const noexcept {
3508 return to_string();
3509 }
3510
3511 template <typename It = Iterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_string() const noexcept -> std::optional<std::basic_string<char_type>> {
3512 if (!static_cast<bool>(*this)) {
3513 return std::nullopt;
3514 }
3515 return to_string();
3516 }
3517
3518 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator std::basic_string_view<char_type>() const noexcept {
3519 return to_view();
3520 }
3521
3522 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE explicit operator std::basic_string<char_type>() const noexcept {
3523 return to_string();
3524 }
3525
3526 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator std::optional<std::basic_string_view<char_type>>() const noexcept {
3527 return to_optional_view();
3528 }
3529
3530 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE explicit operator std::optional<std::basic_string<char_type>>() const noexcept {
3531 return to_optional_string();
3532 }
3533
3534 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static size_t get_id() noexcept {
3535 return Id;
3536 }
3537
3538 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator==(const storage & lhs, std::basic_string_view<char_type> rhs) noexcept {
3539 return bool(lhs) ? lhs.view() == rhs : false;
3540 }
3541 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator!=(const storage & lhs, std::basic_string_view<char_type> rhs) noexcept {
3542 return bool(lhs) ? lhs.view() != rhs : false;
3543 }
3544 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator==(std::basic_string_view<char_type> lhs, const storage & rhs) noexcept {
3545 return bool(rhs) ? lhs == rhs.view() : false;
3546 }
3547 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator!=(std::basic_string_view<char_type> lhs, const storage & rhs) noexcept {
3548 return bool(rhs) ? lhs != rhs.view() : false;
3549 }
3550 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE std::ostream & operator<<(std::ostream & str, const storage & rhs) {
3551 return str << rhs.view();
3552 }
3553 };
3554};
3555
3556#if __cpp_concepts >= 202002L
3557template <typename T> concept capture_group = requires(const T & cap) {
3558 { T::get_id() } -> std::same_as<size_t>;
3559 { cap.view() };
3560 { cap.str() };
3561 { cap.to_string() };
3562 { cap.to_view() };
3563 { cap.unit_size() } -> std::same_as<size_t>;
3564 { cap.size() } -> std::same_as<size_t>;
3565 { static_cast<bool>(cap) };
3566 { cap.data() };
3567 { cap.data_unsafe() };
3568 { cap.begin() };
3569 { cap.end() };
3570};
3571#endif
3572
3573struct capture_not_exists_tag { };
3574
3575constexpr auto capture_not_exists = capture_not_exists_tag{};
3576
3577template <typename... Captures> struct captures;
3578
3579template <typename Head, typename... Tail> struct captures<Head, Tail...>: captures<Tail...> {
3580 Head head{};
3581 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE captures() noexcept { }
3582 template <size_t id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3583 if constexpr (id == Head::get_id()) {
3584 return true;
3585 } else {
3586 return captures<Tail...>::template exists<id>();
3587 }
3588 }
3589 template <typename Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3590 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Name, typename Head::name>) {
3591 return true;
3592 } else {
3593 return captures<Tail...>::template exists<Name>();
3594 }
3595 }
3596#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
3597 template <ctll::fixed_string Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3598#else
3599 template <const auto & Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3600#endif
3601 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<typename Head::name, void>) {
3602 return captures<Tail...>::template exists<Name>();
3603 } else {
3604 if constexpr (Head::name::name.is_same_as(Name)) {
3605 return true;
3606 } else {
3607 return captures<Tail...>::template exists<Name>();
3608 }
3609 }
3610 }
3611 template <size_t id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() noexcept {
3612 if constexpr (id == Head::get_id()) {
3613 return head;
3614 } else {
3615 return captures<Tail...>::template select<id>();
3616 }
3617 }
3618 template <typename Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() noexcept {
3619 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Name, typename Head::name>) {
3620 return head;
3621 } else {
3622 return captures<Tail...>::template select<Name>();
3623 }
3624 }
3625 template <size_t id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3626 if constexpr (id == Head::get_id()) {
3627 return head;
3628 } else {
3629 return captures<Tail...>::template select<id>();
3630 }
3631 }
3632 template <typename Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3633 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Name, typename Head::name>) {
3634 return head;
3635 } else {
3636 return captures<Tail...>::template select<Name>();
3637 }
3638 }
3639#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
3640 template <ctll::fixed_string Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3641#else
3642 template <const auto & Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3643#endif
3644 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<typename Head::name, void>) {
3645 return captures<Tail...>::template select<Name>();
3646 } else {
3647 if constexpr (Head::name::name.is_same_as(Name)) {
3648 return head;
3649 } else {
3650 return captures<Tail...>::template select<Name>();
3651 }
3652 }
3653 }
3654};
3655
3656template <> struct captures<> {
3657 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE captures() noexcept { }
3658 template <size_t> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3659 return false;
3660 }
3661 template <typename> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3662 return false;
3663 }
3664#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
3665 template <ctll::fixed_string> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3666#else
3667 template <const auto &> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static constexpr bool exists() noexcept {
3668#endif
3669 return false;
3670 }
3671 template <size_t> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3672 return capture_not_exists;
3673 }
3674 template <typename> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3675 return capture_not_exists;
3676 }
3677#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
3678 template <ctll::fixed_string> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3679#else
3680 template <const auto &> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto & select() const noexcept {
3681#endif
3682 return capture_not_exists;
3683 }
3684};

3686template <typename Iterator, typename... Captures> class regex_results {
3687 captures<captured_content<0>::template storage<Iterator>, typename Captures::template storage<Iterator>...> _captures{};
3688public:
3689 using char_type = typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::value_type;
3690
3691 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results() noexcept { }
3692 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results(not_matched_tag_t) noexcept { }
3693
3694 // special constructor for deducting
3695 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results(Iterator, ctll::list<Captures...>) noexcept { }
3696
3697 template <size_t Id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto get() const noexcept {
3698 constexpr bool capture_of_provided_id_must_exists = decltype(_captures)::template exists<Id>();
3699 static_assert(capture_of_provided_id_must_exists);
3700
3701 if constexpr (capture_of_provided_id_must_exists) {
3702 return _captures.template select<Id>();
3703 } else {
3704 return false;
3705 }
3706 }
3707 template <typename Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto get() const noexcept {
3708 constexpr bool capture_of_provided_name_must_exists = decltype(_captures)::template exists<Name>();
3709 static_assert(capture_of_provided_name_must_exists);
3710
3711 if constexpr (capture_of_provided_name_must_exists) {
3712 return _captures.template select<Name>();
3713 } else {
3714 return false;
3715 }
3716 }
3717#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
3718 template <ctll::fixed_string Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto get() const noexcept {
3719#else
3720 template <const auto & Name> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto get() const noexcept {
3721#endif
3722 constexpr bool capture_of_provided_name_must_exists = decltype(_captures)::template exists<Name>();
3723 static_assert(capture_of_provided_name_must_exists);
3724
3725 if constexpr (capture_of_provided_name_must_exists) {
3726 return _captures.template select<Name>();
3727 } else {
3728 return false;
3729 }
3730 }
3731 static constexpr size_t count() noexcept {
3732 return sizeof...(Captures) + 1;
3733 }
3734 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results & matched() noexcept {
3735 _captures.template select<0>().matched();
3736 return *this;
3737 }
3738 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results & unmatch() noexcept {
3739 _captures.template select<0>().unmatch();
3740 return *this;
3741 }
3742 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator bool() const noexcept {
3743 return bool(_captures.template select<0>());
3744 }
3745
3746 // implicit conversions
3747 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator std::basic_string_view<char_type>() const noexcept {
3748 return to_view();
3749 }
3750
3751 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE explicit operator std::basic_string<char_type>() const noexcept {
3752 return to_string();
3753 }
3754
3755 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE operator std::optional<std::basic_string_view<char_type>>() const noexcept {
3756 return to_optional_view();
3757 }
3758
3759 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE explicit operator std::optional<std::basic_string<char_type>>() const noexcept {
3760 return to_optional_string();
3761 }
3762
3763 // conversion to numbers
3764#if __has_include(<charconv>)
3765 template <typename R = int, typename... Ts> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_number(Ts && ... args) const noexcept -> R {
3766 return _captures.template select<0>().template to_number<R>(std::forward<Ts>(args)...);
3767 }
3768
3769 template <typename R = int, typename... Ts> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_number(Ts && ... args) const noexcept -> std::optional<R> {
3770 return _captures.template select<0>().template to_optional_number<R>(std::forward<Ts>(args)...);
3771 }
3772#endif
3773
3774 // conversion to basic_string_view
3775 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_view() const noexcept {
3776 return _captures.template select<0>().to_view();
3777 }
3778
3779 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto view() const noexcept {
3780 return _captures.template select<0>().view(); // this should be deprecated (??)
3781 }
3782
3783 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_view() const noexcept {
3784 return _captures.template select<0>().to_optional_view();
3785 }
3786
3787 // conversion to basic_string
3788 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_string() const noexcept {
3789 return _captures.template select<0>().to_string();
3790 }
3791
3792 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto str() const noexcept {
3793 return _captures.template select<0>().to_string(); // this should be deprecated (??)
3794 }
3795
3796 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto to_optional_string() const noexcept {
3797 return _captures.template select<0>().to_optional_string();
3798 }

3802

3804 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE size_t size() const noexcept {
3805 return _captures.template select<0>().size();
3806 }
3807
3808 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE const auto * data() const noexcept {
3809 return _captures.template select<0>().data();
3810 }
3811
3812 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results & set_start_mark(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3813 _captures.template select<0>().set_start(pos);
3814 return *this;
3815 }
3816 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_results & set_end_mark(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3817 _captures.template select<0>().set_end(pos);
3818 return *this;
3819 }
3820 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE Iterator get_end_position() const noexcept {
3821 return _captures.template select<0>().get_end();
3822 }
3823 template <size_t Id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr regex_results & start_capture(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3824 _captures.template select<Id>().set_start(pos);
3825 return *this;
3826 }
3827 template <size_t Id> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr regex_results & end_capture(Iterator pos) noexcept {
3828 _captures.template select<Id>().set_end(pos).matched();
3829 return *this;
3830 }
3831 constexpr auto begin() const noexcept {
3832 return _captures.template select<0>().begin();
3833 }
3834 constexpr auto end() const noexcept {
3835 return _captures.template select<0>().end();
3836 }
3837 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator==(const regex_results & lhs, std::basic_string_view<char_type> rhs) noexcept {
3838 return bool(lhs) ? lhs.view() == rhs : false;
3839 }
3840 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator!=(const regex_results & lhs, std::basic_string_view<char_type> rhs) noexcept {
3841 return bool(lhs) ? lhs.view() != rhs : true;
3842 }
3843 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator==(std::basic_string_view<char_type> lhs, const regex_results & rhs) noexcept {
3844 return bool(rhs) ? lhs == rhs.view() : false;
3845 }
3846 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr bool operator!=(std::basic_string_view<char_type> lhs, const regex_results & rhs) noexcept {
3847 return bool(rhs) ? lhs != rhs.view() : true;
3848 }
3849 friend CTRE_FORCE_INLINE std::ostream & operator<<(std::ostream & str, const regex_results & rhs) {
3850#ifdef CTRE_IN_A_MODULE
3851 auto view = rhs.view();
3852 str.write(view.data(), view.size());
3853 return str;
3854#else
3855 return str << rhs.view();
3856#endif
3857 }
3858};

3860template <size_t Id, typename Iterator, typename... Captures> constexpr auto get(const regex_results<Iterator, Captures...> & results) noexcept {
3861 return results.template get<Id>();
3862}
3863
3864template <typename Iterator, typename... Captures> regex_results(Iterator, ctll::list<Captures...>) -> regex_results<Iterator, Captures...>;
3865
3866template <typename> struct is_regex_results_t: std::false_type { };
3867
3868template <typename Iterator, typename... Captures> struct is_regex_results_t<regex_results<Iterator, Captures...>>: std::true_type { };
3869
3870template <typename T> constexpr bool is_regex_results_v = is_regex_results_t<T>();
3871
3872#if __cpp_concepts >= 201907L
3873template <typename T> concept capture_groups = is_regex_results_v<T>;
3874#endif
