4326template <auto A, typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::character<A>, CB & cb, int64_t start) {
4327 if (A != (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)()) {
4328 if (start < A) {
4329 cb(start, A-1);
4330 }
4331 }
4332 if (A != (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()) {
4333 return A+1;
4334 } else {
4335 return A;
4336 }
4337}
4338
4339template <auto A, auto B, typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::char_range<A,B>, CB & cb, int64_t start) {
4340 if (A != (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)()) {
4341 if (start < A) {
4342 cb(start, A-1);
4343 }
4344 }
4345 if (B != (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()) {
4346 return B+1;
4347 } else {
4348 return B;
4349 }
4350}
4351
4352template <auto Head, auto... Tail, typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::enumeration<Head, Tail...>, CB & cb, int64_t start) {
4353 int64_t nstart = negative_helper(ctre::character<Head>{}, cb, start);
4354 return negative_helper(ctre::enumeration<Tail...>{}, cb, nstart);
4355}
4356
4357template <typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::enumeration<>, CB &, int64_t start) {
4358 return start;
4359}
4360
4361template <typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::set<>, CB &, int64_t start) {
4362 return start;
4363}
4364
4365template <typename PropertyType, PropertyType Property, typename CB>
4366constexpr auto negative_helper(ctre::binary_property<PropertyType, Property>, CB &&, int64_t start) {
4367 return start;
4368}
4369
4370template <typename PropertyType, PropertyType Property, auto Value, typename CB>
4371constexpr auto negative_helper(ctre::property<PropertyType, Property, Value>, CB &&, int64_t start) {
4372 return start;
4373}
4374
4375template <typename Head, typename... Rest, typename CB> constexpr int64_t negative_helper(ctre::set<Head, Rest...>, CB & cb, int64_t start) {
4376 start = negative_helper(Head{}, cb, start);
4377 return negative_helper(ctre::set<Rest...>{}, cb, start);
4378}
4379
4380template <typename Head, typename... Rest, typename CB> constexpr void negative_helper(ctre::negative_set<Head, Rest...>, CB && cb, int64_t start = (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)()) {
4381 start = negative_helper(Head{}, cb, start);
4382 negative_helper(ctre::negative_set<Rest...>{}, std::forward<CB>(cb), start);
4383}
4384
4385template <typename CB> constexpr void negative_helper(ctre::negative_set<>, CB && cb, int64_t start = (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)()) {
4386 if (start < (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()) {
4387 cb(start, (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)());
4388 }

4391// simple fixed set
4392// TODO: this needs some optimizations
4393template <size_t Capacity> class point_set {
4394 struct point {
4395 int64_t low{};
4396 int64_t high{};
4397 constexpr bool operator<(const point & rhs) const {
4398 return low < rhs.low;
4399 }
4400 constexpr point() { }
4401 constexpr point(int64_t l, int64_t h): low{l}, high{h} { }
4402 };
4403 point points[Capacity+1]{};
4404 size_t used{0};
4405 constexpr point * begin() {
4406 return points;
4407 }
4408 constexpr point * begin() const {
4409 return points;
4410 }
4411 constexpr point * end() {
4412 return points + used;
4413 }
4414 constexpr point * end() const {
4415 return points + used;
4416 }
4417 constexpr point * lower_bound(point obj) {
4418 auto first = begin();
4419 auto last = end();
4420 auto it = first;
4421 auto count = std::distance(first, last);
4422 while (count != 0) {
4423 it = first;
4424 auto step = count / 2;
4425 std::advance(it, step);
4426 if (*it < obj) {
4427 first = ++it;
4428 count -= step + 1;
4429 } else {
4430 count = step;
4431 }
4432 }
4433 return it;
4434 }
4435 constexpr point * insert_point(int64_t position, int64_t other) {
4436 point obj{position, other};
4437 auto it = lower_bound(obj);
4438 if (it == end()) {
4439 *it = obj;
4440 used++;
4441 return it;
4442 } else {
4443 auto out = it;
4444 auto e = end();
4445 while (it != e) {
4446 auto tmp = *it;
4447 *it = obj;
4448 obj = tmp;
4449 //std::swap(*it, obj);
4450 it++;
4451 }
4452 auto tmp = *it;
4453 *it = obj;
4454 obj = tmp;
4455 //std::swap(*it, obj);
4456
4457 used++;
4458 return out;
4459 }
4460 }
4461public:
4462 constexpr point_set() { }
4463 constexpr void insert(int64_t low, int64_t high) {
4464 insert_point(low, high);
4465 //insert_point(high, low);
4466 }
4467 constexpr bool check(int64_t low, int64_t high) {
4468 for (const auto & r: *this) {
4469 if (r.low <= low && low <= r.high) {
4470 return true;
4471 } else if (r.low <= high && high <= r.high) {
4472 return true;
4473 } else if (low <= r.low && r.low <= high) {
4474 return true;
4475 } else if (low <= r.high && r.high <= high) {
4476 return true;
4477 }
4478 }
4479 return false;
4480 }
4481
4482
4483 template <auto V> constexpr bool check(ctre::character<V>) {
4484 return check(V,V);
4485 }
4486 template <auto A, auto B> constexpr bool check(ctre::char_range<A,B>) {
4487 return check(A,B);
4488 }
4489 constexpr bool check(can_be_anything) {
4490 return used > 0;
4491 }
4492 template <typename PropertyType, PropertyType Property>
4493 constexpr bool check(ctre::binary_property<PropertyType, Property>) {
4494 return check(can_be_anything{});
4495 }
4496
4497 template <typename PropertyType, PropertyType Property, auto Value>
4498 constexpr bool check(ctre::property<PropertyType, Property, Value>) {
4499 return check(can_be_anything{});
4500 }
4501 template <typename... Content> constexpr bool check(ctre::negative_set<Content...> nset) {
4502 bool collision = false;
4503 negative_helper(nset, [&](int64_t low, int64_t high){
4504 collision |= this->check(low, high);
4505 });
4506 return collision;
4507 }
4508 template <auto... V> constexpr bool check(ctre::enumeration<V...>) {
4509
4510 return (check(V,V) || ... || false);
4511 }
4512 template <typename... Content> constexpr bool check(ctll::list<Content...>) {
4513 return (check(Content{}) || ... || false);
4514 }
4515 template <typename... Content> constexpr bool check(ctre::set<Content...>) {
4516 return (check(Content{}) || ... || false);
4517 }
4518
4519
4520 template <auto V> constexpr void populate(ctre::character<V>) {
4521 insert(V,V);
4522 }
4523 template <auto A, auto B> constexpr void populate(ctre::char_range<A,B>) {
4524 insert(A,B);
4525 }
4526 constexpr void populate(...) {
4527 points[0].low = (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)();
4528 points[0].high = (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)();
4529 used = 1;
4530 }
4531 template <typename... Content> constexpr void populate(ctre::negative_set<Content...> nset) {
4532 negative_helper(nset, [&](int64_t low, int64_t high){
4533 this->insert(low, high);
4534 });
4535 }
4536 template <typename... Content> constexpr void populate(ctre::set<Content...>) {
4537 (populate(Content{}), ...);
4538 }
4539 template <typename... Content> constexpr void populate(ctll::list<Content...>) {
4540 (populate(Content{}), ...);
4541 }
4542};
4543
4544template <typename... A, typename... B> constexpr bool collides(ctll::list<A...> rhs, ctll::list<B...> lhs) {
4545 constexpr size_t capacity = calculate_size_of_first(rhs);
4546
4547 point_set<capacity> set;
4548 set.populate(rhs);
4549
4550 return set.check(lhs);
4551}
4552
4553}
4554
4555#endif

4570template <size_t Limit> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool less_than_or_infinite([[maybe_unused]] size_t i) noexcept {
4571 if constexpr (Limit == 0) {
4572 // infinite
4573 return true;
4574 } else {
4575 return i < Limit;
4576 }
4577}
4578
4579template <size_t Limit> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool less_than([[maybe_unused]] size_t i) noexcept {
4580 if constexpr (Limit == 0) {
4581 // infinite
4582 return false;
4583 } else {
4584 return i < Limit;
4585 }
4586}

4631// matching everything which behave as a one character matcher
4632
4633template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename CharacterLike, typename... Tail, typename = std::enable_if_t<(MatchesCharacter<CharacterLike>::template value<decltype(*std::declval<Iterator>())>)>>
4634constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<CharacterLike, Tail...>) noexcept {
4635 if (current == last) return not_matched;
4636 if (!CharacterLike::match_char(*current, f)) return not_matched;
4637
4638 return evaluate(begin, ++current, last, consumed_something(f), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4639}

4641template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
4642constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<any, Tail...>) noexcept {
4643 if (current == last) return not_matched;
4644
4645 if (multiline_mode(f)) {
4646 // TODO add support for different line ending and unicode (in a future unicode mode)
4647 if (*current == '\n') return not_matched;
4648 }
4649 return evaluate(begin, ++current, last, consumed_something(f), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4650}

4652// matching strings in patterns
4653template <auto... String, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool match_string([[maybe_unused]] Iterator & current, [[maybe_unused]] const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f) {
4654 return ((current != last && character<String>::match_char(*current++, f)) && ... && true);
4655}

4657template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, auto... String, typename... Tail>
4658constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<string<String...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
4659 if (!match_string<String...>(current, last, f)) {
4660 return not_matched;
4661 }
4662
4663 return evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f, sizeof...(String) > 0), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());

4669 if (auto r = evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<HeadOptions, Tail...>())) {

4715template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
4716constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<assert_subject_end_line, Tail...>) noexcept {
4717 if (multiline_mode(f)) {
4718 if (last == current) {
4719 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4720 } else if (*current == '\n' && std::next(current) == last) {
4721 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4722 } else {
4723 return not_matched;
4724 }
4725 } else {
4726 if (last != current) {
4727 return not_matched;
4728 }
4729 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4730 }
4731}

4734constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<assert_line_begin, Tail...>) noexcept {
4735 if (multiline_mode(f)) {
4736 if (begin == current) {
4737 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4738 } else if (*std::prev(current) == '\n') {
4739 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4740 } else {
4741 return not_matched;
4742 }
4743 } else {
4744 if (begin != current) {
4745 return not_matched;
4746 }
4747 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4748 }

4752constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<assert_line_end, Tail...>) noexcept {
4753 if (multiline_mode(f)) {

4756 } else if (*current == '\n') {

4764 if (last != current) {
4765 return not_matched;

4770// matching boundary
4771template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename CharacterLike, typename... Tail>
4772constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<boundary<CharacterLike>, Tail...>) noexcept {
4773
4774 // reason why I need bidirectional iterators or some clever hack
4775 bool before = false;
4776 bool after = false;
4777
4778 static_assert(is_bidirectional(typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::iterator_category{}), "To use boundary in regex you need to provide bidirectional iterator or range.");
4779
4780 if (last != current) {
4781 after = CharacterLike::match_char(*current, f);
4782 }
4783 if (begin != current) {
4784 before = CharacterLike::match_char(*std::prev(current), f);
4785 }
4786
4787 if (before == after) return not_matched;
4788
4789 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4790}

4792// matching not_boundary
4793template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename CharacterLike, typename... Tail>
4794constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<not_boundary<CharacterLike>, Tail...>) noexcept {
4795
4796 // reason why I need bidirectional iterators or some clever hack
4797 bool before = false;
4798 bool after = false;
4799
4800 static_assert(is_bidirectional(typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::iterator_category{}), "To use boundary in regex you need to provide bidirectional iterator or range.");
4801
4802 if (last != current) {
4803 after = CharacterLike::match_char(*current, f);
4804 }
4805 if (begin != current) {
4806 before = CharacterLike::match_char(*std::prev(current), f);
4807 }
4808
4809 if (before != after) return not_matched;
4810
4811 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4812}

4814// lazy repeat
4815template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, size_t A, size_t B, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
4816constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<lazy_repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
4817
4818 if constexpr (B != 0 && A > B) {
4819 return not_matched;
4820 } else {
4821 const Iterator backup_current = current;
4822
4823 size_t i{0};
4824
4825 while (less_than<A>(i)) {
4826 auto outer_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, not_empty_match(f), captures, ctll::list<Content..., end_cycle_mark>());
4827
4828 if (!outer_result) return not_matched;
4829
4830 captures = outer_result.unmatch();
4831 current = outer_result.get_end_position();
4832
4833 ++i;
4834 }
4835
4836 if (auto outer_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f, backup_current != current), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>())) {
4837 return outer_result;
4838 }
4839
4840 while (less_than_or_infinite<B>(i)) {
4841 auto inner_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, not_empty_match(f), captures, ctll::list<Content..., end_cycle_mark>());
4842
4843 if (!inner_result) return not_matched;
4844
4845 auto outer_result = evaluate(begin, inner_result.get_end_position(), last, consumed_something(f), inner_result.unmatch(), ctll::list<Tail...>());
4846
4847 if (outer_result) {
4848 return outer_result;
4849 }
4850
4851 captures = inner_result.unmatch();
4852 current = inner_result.get_end_position();
4853
4854 ++i;
4855 }
4856
4857 // rest of regex
4858 return evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4859 }
4860}
4861
4862// possessive repeat
4863template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, size_t A, size_t B, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
4864constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<possessive_repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
4865
4866 if constexpr ((B != 0) && (A > B)) {
4867 return not_matched;
4868 } else {
4869 const auto backup_current = current;
4870
4871 for (size_t i{0}; less_than_or_infinite<B>(i); ++i) {
4872 // try as many of inner as possible and then try outer once
4873 auto inner_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, not_empty_match(f), captures, ctll::list<Content..., end_cycle_mark>());
4874
4875 if (!inner_result) {
4876 if (!less_than<A>(i)) break;
4877 return not_matched;
4878 }
4879
4880 captures = inner_result.unmatch();
4881 current = inner_result.get_end_position();
4882 }
4883
4884 return evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f, backup_current != current), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4885 }
4886}
4887
4888// (gready) repeat
4889template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, size_t A, size_t B, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
4890#ifdef CTRE_MSVC_GREEDY_WORKAROUND
4891constexpr inline void evaluate_recursive(R & result, size_t i, const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...> stack) noexcept {
4892#else
4893constexpr inline R evaluate_recursive(size_t i, const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...> stack) noexcept {
4894#endif
4895 if (less_than_or_infinite<B>(i)) {
4896
4897 // a*ab
4898 // aab
4899
4900 if (auto inner_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, not_empty_match(f), captures, ctll::list<Content..., end_cycle_mark>())) {
4901 // TODO MSVC issue:
4902 // if I uncomment this return it will not fail in constexpr (but the matching result will not be correct)
4903 // return inner_result
4904 // I tried to add all constructors to R but without any success
4905 auto tmp_current = current;
4906 tmp_current = inner_result.get_end_position();
4907 #ifdef CTRE_MSVC_GREEDY_WORKAROUND
4908 evaluate_recursive(result, i+1, begin, tmp_current, last, f, inner_result.unmatch(), stack);
4909 if (result) {
4910 return;
4911 }
4912 #else
4913 if (auto rec_result = evaluate_recursive(i+1, begin, tmp_current, last, f, inner_result.unmatch(), stack)) {
4914 return rec_result;
4915 }
4916 #endif
4917 }
4918 }
4919 #ifdef CTRE_MSVC_GREEDY_WORKAROUND
4920 result = evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4921 #else
4922 return evaluate(begin, current, last, consumed_something(f), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
4923 #endif
4924}
4925
4926// (greedy) repeat
4927template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, size_t A, size_t B, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
4928constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, [[maybe_unused]] const flags & f, R captures, [[maybe_unused]] ctll::list<repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...> stack) {
4929
4930 if constexpr ((B != 0) && (A > B)) {
4931 return not_matched;
4932 }
4933
4934#ifndef CTRE_DISABLE_GREEDY_OPT
4935 else if constexpr (!collides(calculate_first(Content{}...), calculate_first(Tail{}...))) {
4936 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<possessive_repeat<A,B,Content...>, Tail...>());
4937 }
4938#endif
4939 else {
4940 // A..B
4941 size_t i{0};
4942 while (less_than<A>(i)) {
4943 auto inner_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, not_empty_match(f), captures, ctll::list<Content..., end_cycle_mark>());
4944
4945 if (!inner_result) return not_matched;
4946
4947 captures = inner_result.unmatch();
4948 current = inner_result.get_end_position();
4949
4950 ++i;
4951 }
4952
4953#ifdef CTRE_MSVC_GREEDY_WORKAROUND
4954 R result;
4955 evaluate_recursive(result, i, begin, current, last, f, captures, stack);
4956 return result;
4957#else
4958 return evaluate_recursive(i, begin, current, last, f, captures, stack);
4959#endif
4960 }
4961
4962}

4982// backreference support (match agains content of iterators)
4983template <typename Iterator> struct string_match {
4984 Iterator position;
4985 bool match;
4986};
4987
4988template <typename Iterator, typename EndIterator> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE string_match<Iterator> match_against_range(Iterator current, const EndIterator last, Iterator range_current, const Iterator range_end, flags) noexcept {
4989 while (last != current && range_end != range_current) {
4990 if (*current == *range_current) {
4991 current++;
4992 range_current++;
4993 } else {
4994 return {current, false};
4995 }
4996 }
4997 return {current, range_current == range_end};
4998}
4999
5000// backreference with name
5001template <typename R, typename Id, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
5002constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<back_reference_with_name<Id>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5003
5004 if (const auto ref = captures.template get<Id>()) {
5005 if (auto result = match_against_range(current, last, ref.begin(), ref.end(), f); result.match) {
5006 return evaluate(begin, result.position, last, consumed_something(f, ref.begin() != ref.end()), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5007 }
5008 }
5009 return not_matched;
5010}
5011
5012// backreference
5013template <typename R, size_t Id, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
5014constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<back_reference<Id>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5015
5016 if (const auto ref = captures.template get<Id>()) {
5017 if (auto result = match_against_range(current, last, ref.begin(), ref.end(), f); result.match) {
5018 return evaluate(begin, result.position, last, consumed_something(f, ref.begin() != ref.end()), captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5019 }
5020 }
5021 return not_matched;
5022}
5023
5024// end of lookahead
5025template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
5026constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator, Iterator, const EndIterator, flags, R captures, ctll::list<end_lookahead_mark>) noexcept {
5027 // TODO check interaction with non-empty flag
5028 return captures.matched();
5029}
5030
5031template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Tail>
5032constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator, Iterator, const EndIterator, flags, R captures, ctll::list<end_lookbehind_mark>) noexcept {
5033 // TODO check interaction with non-empty flag
5034 return captures.matched();
5035}
5036
5037// lookahead positive
5038template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
5039constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<lookahead_positive<Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5040
5041 if (auto lookahead_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<sequence<Content...>, end_lookahead_mark>())) {
5042 captures = lookahead_result.unmatch();
5043 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5044 } else {
5045 return not_matched;
5046 }
5047}
5048
5049// lookahead negative
5050template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
5051constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<lookahead_negative<Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5052
5053 if (auto lookahead_result = evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<sequence<Content...>, end_lookahead_mark>())) {
5054 return not_matched;
5055 } else {
5056 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5057 }
5058}
5059
5060// lookbehind positive
5061constexpr bool is_at_least_bidirectional(std::input_iterator_tag) {
5062 return false;
5063}
5064
5065constexpr bool is_at_least_bidirectional(std::bidirectional_iterator_tag) {
5066 return true;
5067}
5068
5069template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
5070constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<lookbehind_positive<Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5071 static_assert(is_at_least_bidirectional(typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::iterator_category{}), "to use lookbehind you must provide bi-directional iterator");
5072
5073 if (auto lookbehind_result = evaluate(std::make_reverse_iterator(last), std::make_reverse_iterator(current), std::make_reverse_iterator(begin), f, captures, ctll::list<sequence<Content...>, end_lookbehind_mark>())) {
5074 captures = lookbehind_result.unmatch();
5075 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5076 } else {
5077 return not_matched;
5078 }
5079}
5080
5081// lookbehind negative
5082template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
5083constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<lookbehind_negative<Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5084 static_assert(is_at_least_bidirectional(typename std::iterator_traits<Iterator>::iterator_category{}), "to use negative lookbehind you must provide bi-directional iterator");
5085
5086 if (auto lookbehind_result = evaluate(std::make_reverse_iterator(last), std::make_reverse_iterator(current), std::make_reverse_iterator(begin), f, captures, ctll::list<sequence<Content...>, end_lookbehind_mark>())) {
5087 return not_matched;
5088 } else {
5089 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5090 }
5091}
5092
5093template <typename...> constexpr auto dependent_false = false;
5094
5095// atomic_group<...> is just transformation to possessive_repeat<1,1,...>
5096template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename... Content, typename... Tail>
5097constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<atomic_group<Content...>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5098 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f, captures, ctll::list<possessive_repeat<1,1,Content...>, Tail...>{});
5099}
5100
5101// switching modes
5102template <typename R, typename BeginIterator, typename Iterator, typename EndIterator, typename Mode, typename... Tail>
5103constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE R evaluate(const BeginIterator begin, Iterator current, const EndIterator last, const flags & f, R captures, ctll::list<mode_switch<Mode>, Tail...>) noexcept {
5104 return evaluate(begin, current, last, f + Mode{}, captures, ctll::list<Tail...>());
5105}

5132template <typename BeginIterator, typename EndIterator, typename RE, typename ResultIterator = BeginIterator> struct regex_iterator {
5133 using value_type = decltype(RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(std::declval<BeginIterator>(), std::declval<EndIterator>()));
5134 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
5135 using pointer = void;
5136 using reference = const value_type &;
5137 using difference_type = int;
5138
5139 BeginIterator orig_begin{};
5140 BeginIterator current{};
5141 EndIterator end{};
5142 value_type current_match{};
5143
5144 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator() noexcept = default;
5145 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator(const regex_iterator &) noexcept = default;
5146 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator(regex_iterator &&) noexcept = default;
5147
5148 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator(BeginIterator begin, EndIterator last) noexcept: orig_begin{begin}, current{begin}, end{last}, current_match{RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(current, last)} {
5149 if (current_match) {
5150 current = current_match.template get<0>().end();
5151 }
5152 }
5153
5154 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator & operator=(const regex_iterator &) noexcept = default;
5155 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator & operator=(regex_iterator &&) noexcept = default;
5156
5157 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE const value_type & operator*() const noexcept {
5158 return current_match;
5159 }
5160 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator & operator++() noexcept {
5161 if (current == end) {
5162 current_match = decltype(current_match){};
5163 return *this;
5164 }
5165
5166 current_match = RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(orig_begin, current, end);
5167
5168 if (current_match) {
5169 current = current_match.template get<0>().end();
5170 }
5171 return *this;
5172 }
5173 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_iterator operator++(int) noexcept {
5174 auto previous = *this;
5175 this->operator++();
5176 return previous;
5177 }
5178 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5179 return left.current == right.current;
5180 }
5181 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5182 return !(left.current == right.current);
5183 }
5184 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5185 return left.current < right.current;
5186 }
5187 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5188 return left.current > right.current;
5189 }
5190 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<=(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5191 return left.current <= right.current;
5192 }
5193 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>=(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5194 return left.current >= right.current;
5195 }
5196 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, regex_end_iterator) noexcept {
5197 return !bool(left.current_match);
5198 }
5199 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(regex_end_iterator, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5200 return !bool(right.current_match);
5201 }
5202 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, regex_end_iterator) noexcept {
5203 return bool(left.current_match);
5204 }
5205 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(regex_end_iterator, const regex_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5206 return bool(right.current_match);
5207 }
5208};

5210template <typename BeginIterator, typename EndIterator, typename RE, typename ResultIterator = BeginIterator> struct regex_split_iterator {
5211 using value_type = decltype(RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(std::declval<BeginIterator>(), std::declval<EndIterator>()));
5212 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
5213 using pointer = void;
5214 using reference = const value_type &;
5215 using difference_type = int;
5216
5217 BeginIterator orig_begin{};
5218 BeginIterator current{};
5219 EndIterator end{};
5220 value_type current_match{};
5221 bool last_match{false};
5222
5223 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void modify_match() {
5224 auto tmp = current_match.template get<0>().end();
5225 current_match.set_end_mark(current_match.template get<0>().begin());
5226 current_match.set_start_mark(current);
5227 current = tmp;
5228 }
5229
5230 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE void match_rest() {
5231 // the end is there set by search_method
5232 current_match.set_start_mark(current);
5233 current_match.matched();
5234 current = current_match.template get<0>().end();
5235 last_match = true;
5236 }
5237
5238 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator() noexcept = default;
5239 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator(const regex_split_iterator &) noexcept = default;
5240 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator(regex_split_iterator &&) noexcept = default;
5241
5242 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator(BeginIterator begin, EndIterator last) noexcept: orig_begin{begin}, current{begin}, end{last}, current_match{RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(current, last)} {
5243 if (current_match) {
5244 modify_match();
5245 } else {
5246 match_rest();
5247 }
5248 }
5249
5250 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator & operator=(const regex_split_iterator &) noexcept = default;
5251 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator & operator=(regex_split_iterator &&) noexcept = default;
5252
5253 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE const value_type & operator*() const noexcept {
5254 return current_match;
5255 }
5256 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator & operator++() noexcept {
5257 if (current == end && last_match) {
5258 current_match = decltype(current_match){};
5259 return *this;
5260 }
5261
5262 current_match = RE::template exec_with_result_iterator<ResultIterator>(orig_begin, current, end);
5263
5264 if (current_match) {
5265 modify_match();
5266 } else {
5267 match_rest();
5268 }
5269 return *this;
5270 }
5271 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regex_split_iterator operator++(int) noexcept {
5272 auto previous = *this;
5273 this->operator++();
5274 return previous;
5275 }
5276 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5277 return left.current == right.current;
5278 }
5279 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5280 return !(left.current == right.current);
5281 }
5282 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5283 return left.current < right.current;
5284 }
5285 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5286 return left.current > right.current;
5287 }
5288 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<=(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5289 return left.current <= right.current;
5290 }
5291 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>=(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5292 return left.current >= right.current;
5293 }
5294 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, regex_end_iterator) noexcept {
5295 return !bool(left.current_match);
5296 }
5297 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(regex_end_iterator, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5298 return !bool(right.current_match);
5299 }
5300 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & left, regex_end_iterator) noexcept {
5301 return bool(left.current_match);
5302 }
5303 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(regex_end_iterator, const regex_split_iterator<BeginIterator, EndIterator, RE, ResultIterator> & right) noexcept {
5304 return bool(right.current_match);
5305 }
5306};

5348template <typename Range, typename RE> struct multi_subject_range {
5349 struct end_iterator { };
5350
5351 using first_type = decltype(std::declval<Range>().begin());
5352 using last_type = decltype(std::declval<Range>().end());
5353
5354 struct iterator {
5355 using value_type = decltype(RE::exec(std::declval<typename std::iterator_traits<first_type>::value_type>()));
5356 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
5357 using reference = const value_type &;
5358 using pointer = const value_type *;
5359 using difference_type = int;
5360
5361 first_type first{};
5362 last_type last{};
5363 value_type current_result{};
5364
5365 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE iterator() noexcept = default;
5366 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE iterator(first_type f, last_type l) noexcept: first{f}, last{l}, current_result{find_first()} { }
5367
5368 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE value_type find_first() noexcept {
5369 while (first != last) {
5370 if (auto res = RE::exec(*first)) return res;
5371 else ++first;
5372 }
5373 return {};
5374 }
5375
5376 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE reference operator*() const noexcept {
5377 return current_result;
5378 }
5379
5380 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE pointer operator->() const noexcept {
5381 return &current_result;
5382 }
5383
5384 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE iterator & operator++() noexcept {
5385 ++first;
5386 current_result = find_first();
5387 return *this;
5388 }
5389 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE iterator operator++(int) noexcept {
5390 auto previous = *this;
5391 this->operator++();
5392 return previous;
5393 }
5394
5395 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5396 return left.first == right.first;
5397 }
5398 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5399 return !(left.first == right.first);
5400 }
5401 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5402 return left.first < right.first;
5403 }
5404 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5405 return left.first > right.first;
5406 }
5407 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator<=(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5408 return left.first <= right.first;
5409 }
5410 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator>=(const iterator & left, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5411 return left.first >= right.first;
5412 }
5413 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(const iterator & left, end_iterator) noexcept {
5414 return left.first == left.last;
5415 }
5416 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator==(end_iterator, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5417 return right.first == right.last;
5418 }
5419 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(const iterator & left, end_iterator) noexcept {
5420 return left.first != left.last;
5421 }
5422 friend constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE bool operator!=(end_iterator, const iterator & right) noexcept {
5423 return right.first == right.last;
5424 }
5425 };
5426
5427 Range range{};
5428
5429 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE multi_subject_range() noexcept = default;
5430 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE multi_subject_range(Range r) noexcept: range{r} { }
5431
5432 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto begin() const noexcept {
5433 return iterator{range.begin(), range.end()};
5434 }
5435 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto end() const noexcept {
5436 return end_iterator{};
5437 }
5438};

5441template <typename... Ts> constexpr bool is_range<multi_subject_range<Ts...>> = true;
5442

5509template <typename T> class RangeLikeType {
5510 template <typename Y> static auto test(Y *) -> decltype(std::declval<const Y &>().begin(), std::declval<const Y &>().end(), std::true_type());
5511 template <typename> static auto test(...) -> std::false_type;
5512
5513public:
5514 static constexpr bool value = decltype(test<std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_const_t<T>>>(nullptr))::value;
5515};
5516
5517struct match_method {
5518 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin orig_begin, IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5519 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5520
5521 return evaluate(orig_begin, begin, end, Modifier{}, return_type<result_iterator, RE>{}, ctll::list<start_mark, RE, assert_subject_end, end_mark, accept>());
5522 }
5523
5524 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5525 return exec<Modifier, ResultIterator>(begin, begin, end, RE{});
5526 }
5527};
5528
5529struct search_method {
5530 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin orig_begin, IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5531 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5532
5533 constexpr bool fixed = starts_with_anchor(Modifier{}, ctll::list<RE>{});
5534
5535 auto it = begin;
5536
5537 for (; end != it && !fixed; ++it) {
5538 if (auto out = evaluate(orig_begin, it, end, Modifier{}, return_type<result_iterator, RE>{}, ctll::list<start_mark, RE, end_mark, accept>())) {
5539 return out;
5540 }
5541 }
5542
5543 // in case the RE is empty or fixed
5544 auto out = evaluate(orig_begin, it, end, Modifier{}, return_type<result_iterator, RE>{}, ctll::list<start_mark, RE, end_mark, accept>());
5545
5546 // ALERT: ugly hack
5547 // propagate end even if it didn't match (this is needed for split function)
5548 if (!out) out.set_end_mark(it);
5549 return out;
5550 }
5551
5552 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5553 return exec<Modifier, ResultIterator>(begin, begin, end, RE{});
5554 }
5555};
5556
5557struct starts_with_method {
5558 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin orig_begin, IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5559 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5560 return evaluate(orig_begin, begin, end, Modifier{}, return_type<result_iterator, RE>{}, ctll::list<start_mark, RE, end_mark, accept>());
5561 }
5562
5563 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5564 return exec<Modifier, ResultIterator>(begin, begin, end, RE{});
5565 }
5566};
5567
5568// wrapper which calls search on input
5569struct range_method {
5570 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5571 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5572 using wrapped_regex = regular_expression<RE, search_method, Modifier>;
5573
5574 return regex_range<IteratorBegin, IteratorEnd, wrapped_regex, result_iterator>(begin, end);
5575 }
5576};
5577
5578struct tokenize_method {
5579 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5580 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5581 using wrapped_regex = regular_expression<RE, starts_with_method, Modifier>;
5582
5583 return regex_range<IteratorBegin, IteratorEnd, wrapped_regex, result_iterator>(begin, end);
5584 }
5585};
5586
5587struct split_method {
5588 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5589 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5590 using wrapped_regex = regular_expression<RE, search_method, Modifier>;
5591
5592 return regex_split_range<IteratorBegin, IteratorEnd, wrapped_regex, result_iterator>(begin, end);
5593 }
5594};
5595
5596struct iterator_method {
5597 template <typename Modifier = singleline, typename ResultIterator = void, typename RE, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end, RE) noexcept {
5598 using result_iterator = std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<ResultIterator, void>, IteratorBegin, ResultIterator>;
5599 using wrapped_regex = regular_expression<RE, search_method, Modifier>;
5600
5601 return regex_iterator<IteratorBegin, IteratorEnd, wrapped_regex, result_iterator>(begin, end);
5602 }
5603 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec() noexcept {
5604 return regex_end_iterator{};
5605 }
5606};

5608CTRE_EXPORT template <typename RE, typename Method, typename Modifier> struct regular_expression {
5609 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regular_expression() noexcept { }
5610 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE regular_expression(RE) noexcept { }
5611
5612 template <typename ResultIterator, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec_with_result_iterator(IteratorBegin orig_begin, IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end) noexcept {
5613 return Method::template exec<Modifier, ResultIterator>(orig_begin, begin, end, RE{});
5614 }
5615 template <typename ResultIterator, typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec_with_result_iterator(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end) noexcept {
5616 return Method::template exec<Modifier, ResultIterator>(begin, end, RE{});
5617 }
5618 template <typename Range> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto multi_exec(Range && range) noexcept {
5619 return multi_subject_range<Range, regular_expression>{std::forward<Range>(range)};
5620 }
5621 constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec() noexcept {
5622 return Method::exec();
5623 }
5624 template <typename IteratorBegin, typename IteratorEnd> constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE static auto exec(IteratorBegin begin, IteratorEnd end) noexcept {
5625 return Method::template exec<Modifier>(begin, end, RE{});
5626 }
5627 static constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto exec(const char * s) noexcept {
5628 return Method::template exec<Modifier>(s, zero_terminated_string_end_iterator(), RE{});
5629 }
5630 static constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto exec(const wchar_t * s) noexcept {
5631 return Method::template exec<Modifier>(s, zero_terminated_string_end_iterator(), RE{});
5632 }

5634 return exec(sv.begin(), sv.end());
5635 }
5636 static constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto exec(std::wstring_view sv) noexcept {
5637 return exec(sv.begin(), sv.end());
5638 }

5643#endif

5646 }
5647 static constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto exec(std::u32string_view sv) noexcept {
5648 return exec(sv.begin(), sv.end());
5649 }
5650 template <typename Range, typename = typename std::enable_if<RangeLikeType<Range>::value>::type> static constexpr CTRE_FORCE_INLINE auto exec(Range && range) noexcept {
5651 return exec(std::begin(range), std::end(range));
5652 }

5656 return exec(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
5657 }
5658 // api for pattern matching
5659 template <typename... Args> CTRE_FORCE_INLINE constexpr auto try_extract(Args &&... args) const noexcept {
5660 return exec(std::forward<Args>(args)...);

5728// error reporting of problematic position in a regex
5729template <size_t> struct problem_at_position; // do not define!
5730
5731template <> struct problem_at_position<~static_cast<size_t>(0)> {
5732 constexpr operator bool() const noexcept {
5733 return true;
5734 }
5735};

5737#if CTRE_CNTTP_COMPILER_CHECK
5738#define CTRE_REGEX_INPUT_TYPE ctll::fixed_string
5739#define CTRE_REGEX_TEMPLATE_COPY_TYPE auto
5740#else
5741#define CTRE_REGEX_INPUT_TYPE const auto &
5742#define CTRE_REGEX_TEMPLATE_COPY_TYPE const auto &
5743#endif
5744
5745template <CTRE_REGEX_TEMPLATE_COPY_TYPE input> struct regex_builder {
5746 static constexpr auto _input = input;
5747 using result = typename ctll::parser<ctre::pcre, _input, ctre::pcre_actions>::template output<pcre_context<>>;
5748
5749 static constexpr auto n = result::is_correct ? ~static_cast<size_t>(0) : result::position;
5750
5751 static_assert(result::is_correct && problem_at_position<n>{}, "Regular Expression contains syntax error.");
5752
5753 using type = ctll::conditional<result::is_correct, decltype(ctll::front(typename result::output_type::stack_type())), ctll::list<reject>>;
5754};
5755
